esses the difference in perceptions, which is essential.\n\nNext, the sample responses all include specific examples. For instance, one sample says women prefer pastel knits and pleated skirts, while men like white T-shirts with pleated skirts. Another sample mentions women's focus on silhouettes and details versus men's preference for simple, cute looks. So, another criterion could be whether the response includes specific examples.\n\nThe reference response also talks about the underlying reasons, like differing aesthetic preferences. So, a third criterion might be whether the response explains the reasons behind the differences.\n\nLooking at the samples, some responses mention the cultural or societal influences. For example, one sample says women focus on balance and details, while men prefer symbolic elements. Another sample talks about trends and symbols. So, a fourth criterion could be whether the response discusses cultural or societal factors.\n\nAnother point from the reference is that the response is concise, under 300 characters. So, a fifth criterion could be whether the response is concise and within the character limit.\n\nThe reference also mentions that the response is self-contained, not relying on external information. So, a sixth criterion could be whether the response is self-contained and doesn't require additional context.\n\nThe samples include both men's and women's perspectives, so a seventh criterion could be whether the response clearly differentiates between the two groups' views.\n\nFinally, the reference response is structured with a clear comparison, so a eighth criterion could be whether the response is structured to compare the two perspectives directly.\n\nNow, I need to make sure each criterion is binary (yes/no), specific to the prompt, and not vague. Also, avoid generic advice. Let me check each one again to ensure they fit.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 남녀의 귀여운 패션 인식 차이를 구체적인 예를 포함하여 300자 이내로 명확히 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"specific_examples\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성과 남성의 시각 차이에 대한 구체적인 패션 아이템 예시를 포함한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"reasoning\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 차이의 근본 원인(예: 심미관, 문화적 배경)을 간략히 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 남녀의 패션 인식 차이에 대한 사회적/문화적 배경을 언급한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"conciseness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 300자 이내로 간결하게 구성되어 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"self_containment\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 외부 정보에 의존하지 않고 자체적으로 완성되어 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"perspective_distinction\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성과 남성의 시각을 구분하여 독립적으로 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 차이점 비교를 위한 구조화된 형식(예: 대비, 예시)을 갖춘다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
