nction's ontological status, the measurement problem, and the complementarity principle.\n\nSo, the main criteria should revolve around these aspects. Let me list possible criteria:\n\n1. **Wave Function Interpretation**: Whether the response addresses the ontological status of the wave function (real vs a mathematical tool).\n2. **Determinism vs Probability**: Whether the response distinguishes between deterministic and probabilistic views.\n3. **Measurement and Collapse**: Whether the response discusses the role of measurement and the collapse of the wave function.\n4. **Complementarity Principle**: Whether the response mentions Bohr's complementarity principle.\n5. **Realism vs Instrumentalism**: Whether the response differentiates between realist and instrumentalist views of the wave function.\n6. **Deterministic Evolution**: Whether the response acknowledges the deterministic evolution of the wave function (Schrödinger's view).\n7. **Role of Observation**: Whether the response addresses how observation affects the system (Bohr's view).\n8. **Historical Context**: Whether the response includes the historical context of their debate, like the Solvay Conference or the EPR paradox.\n\nNow, I need to ensure each criterion is specific, binary, and not generic. Let me check if these are covered in the reference and samples. The reference and samples do discuss these points, so these criteria should work. Each should be a YES/NO check based on whether the response addresses the specific aspect.\n\nI need to make sure the criteria are in Korean, as per the user's request. Also, the JSON structure must be correct with the required fields. Let me structure each criterion with the correct ID, axis, importance, weight, polarity, and text in Korean. The self_contained field should be true for each.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 양자역학의 해석 차이에 대한 철학적 배경을 정확히 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 슈뢰딩거와 보어의 파동함수 해석 차이를 명확히 구분한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 결정론 vs 확률론적 세계관의 대립을 정확히 제시한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 측정의 역할과 파동함수 붕괴에 대한 논쟁을 다룬다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 보어의 상보성 원리와 슈뢰딩거의 연속적 실재관을 구분한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 양자역학의 수학적 형식과 해석적 차이를 구분한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 역사적 맥락(솔베이 회의, 고양이 역설 등)을 적절히 반영한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 양자 해석의 현대적 영향(다세계 이론, 얽힘 등)을 언급한다.\",\n      