{"prompt_id": "prompt_9c5c95c4b8ba", "pair_id": "pair_1428c31c4a32", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:4e39ec]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:b1ae58]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:2884f6]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:12a061]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a recursive rubric designer for LLM-as-a-judge. The user provided a prompt, a reference response, and some sample responses. My task is to come up with 8 criteria that are specific to the prompt, binary (YES/NO), and not vague. Let me start by understanding the user's question.\n\nThe user is asking whether an elderly person should definitely give up their seat on a bus when the user has a cast on their leg from surgery. The reference response emphasizes considering the individual's physical condition and prioritizing the user's safety. The sample responses all agree that the user doesn't need to give up the seat, focusing on their health and safety.\n\nNow, I need to identify the key aspects that the reference and samples address. The main points seem to be: following the instruction, prioritizing the user's health, considering the elderly person's actual condition, maintaining politeness, avoiding conflict, ensuring safety, using appropriate communication, and adhering to norms.\n\nLet me list possible criteria. The first one is instruction following. The response must address the user's specific situation. Then, prioritizing the user's health and safety. Next, considering the elderly person's actual condition. Then, maintaining politeness and appropriate communication. Also, avoiding conflict and ensuring safety. Maybe another criterion about using the correct norms or guidelines. And finally, ensuring that the response is concise and to the point.\n\nWait, the user wants 8 criteria. Let me check each sample response. They all mention the user's health, the elderly person's condition, politeness, communication, safety, and norms. So maybe the criteria can be:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response directly address the user's specific situation?\n2. Prioritizing User's Health: Does it emphasize the user's health and safety?\n3. Considering Elderly's Actual Condition: Does it take into account the elderly person's actual physical state?\n4. Politeness and Appropriate Communication: Does it suggest polite and appropriate ways to communicate?\n5. Avoiding Conflict: Does it avoid creating conflict by suggesting alternatives?\n6. Safety First: Does it prioritize safety over the general norm?\n7. Adhering to Norms: Does it follow the general norms but with exceptions?\n8. Conciseness and Clarity: Is the response clear and to the point without unnecessary details?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary and specific. Let me adjust them to fit the prompt. For example, \"Prioritizing User's Health\" would be a yes if the response emphasizes the user's health. \"Considering Elderly's Actual Condition\" would be yes if the response acknowledges the elderly person's actual state. \"Safety First\" would check if safety is the main concern. \"Adhering to Norms\" would check if the response follows general norms but with exceptions. \"Politeness and Communication\" would check if the response suggests polite communication methods. \"Avoiding Conflict\" would check if the response offers alternatives to avoid conflict. \"Instruction Following\" would check if the response directly addresses the user's situation. \"Conciseness\" would check if the response is clear and to the point.\n\nI need to ensure that each criterion is specific to the prompt and not generic. Let me finalize the 8 criteria based on this analysis.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 사용자의 상황(다리 수술, 기브스)과 어르신의 실제 상태를 직접 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"health_priority\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 사용자의 건강과 안전을 우선적으로 강조합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"elderly_condition_assessment\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 어르신의 실제 신체 상태(건강 여부)를 고려합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"polite_communication\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 정중한 의사소통 방법(예: 사정 설명)을 제안합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"conflict_avoidance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 갈등을 피하는 대안(예: 주변 승객 요청)을 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"safety_first\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 사용자의 안전을 위기 상황에 우선시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"norm_compliance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일반 규범을 존중하면서도 예외 상황을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"conciseness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 핵심 메시지에 집중하고, 불필요한 추가 설명을 피합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_634e206a4e4c", "pair_id": "pair_147e6dfb0bb1", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:91a2a5]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:f22334]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:f8e5cd]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:170cd0]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, let's tackle this. The user wants me to create 8 criteria for evaluating responses to the given prompt. The prompt is to write a part of a female protagonist's dialogue in a situation where she's trying to catch someone who wants to go home. The reference response and sample responses are provided, so I need to analyze them to figure out what's important.\n\nFirst, I need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and can be judged as YES/NO. They should be binary and not vague. Let me look at the reference response. It's a conversation between the protagonist and another character, with the protagonist trying to convince the other person to stay. The dialogue shows the protagonist's determination to stop the other person from leaving, using a specific scenario (not liking potato bread) as a reason.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all have different tones and styles. Some are more direct, others more emotional. The key elements seem to be the protagonist's intent to stop the other person, the use of a specific reason (like the potato bread), and the emotional tone of the dialogue.\n\nSo, the first criterion should be about following the instruction. The response must include the protagonist trying to stop the other person from leaving. That's essential, so that's R1.\n\nNext, the dialogue should reflect the specific scenario mentioned in the prompt. The reference uses the potato bread as a reason, so R2 could be about including that specific element.\n\nAnother point is the emotional tone. The reference has a determined and emotional tone, so R3 could check if the dialogue conveys that.\n\nThe dialogue should be concise and natural, not forced. The reference is short and realistic, so R4 could be about naturalness.\n\nThe response should have a clear conflict or tension, which the reference does. So R5 is about showing conflict.\n\nThe dialogue should be in the protagonist's voice, showing her personality. The reference uses a determined and persuasive tone, so R6 checks for that.\n\nThe response should be self-contained, not relying on external context. The reference is standalone, so R7 is about self-containment.\n\nLastly, the dialogue should be relevant to the situation, which the reference clearly is. So R8 checks relevance.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific, binary, and not generic. Avoid advice like \"be concise\" and instead focus on specific elements from the reference and samples. Also, ensure that the criteria are weighted and have the correct polarity. The importance is essential for the first two, then maybe important for the rest. Weights can be adjusted accordingly.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '집에 가려고 하는 사람을 붙잡는 상황'에서 여주인공의 대사를 포함해야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"scenario_specificity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '감자빵 싫어하는 사람'이라는 구체적 상황을 반영해야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"emotional_tone\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여주인공의 결단력과 감정적 유대감을 드러내야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"dialogue_naturalness\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 현실적인 대화 패턴을 따르고, 강요되지 않은 표현이어야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"conflict_resolution\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 상대방의 이탈을 막는 갈등을 구체적으로 표현해야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"character_voice\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여주인공의 성격(결단력, 설득력)을 반영한 대사를 포함해야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"self_containment\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 외부 맥락에 의존하지 않고 독립적인 대사를 제공해야 한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"situation_relevance\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '집에 가려고 하는 사람을 붙잡는' 상황과 직접적으로 관련되어야 한다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
