ention the Extra Field mechanism, the TLV (Type-Length-Value) structure, the use of Header IDs, and how the parser skips unknown fields by their size. They also discuss ZIP64, different Header IDs for various extensions, and the versioning in the headers.\n\nSo, the main criteria should revolve around the presence of the Extra Field, the TLV structure, the Header ID, the ability to add multiple Extra Fields, the use of versioning, the handling of unknown fields, the use of ZIP64, and the overall extensibility.\n\nLet me list possible criteria:\n\n1. **Presence of Extra Field**: Does the response mention the Extra Field in the header?\n2. **TLV Structure**: Does it describe the Extra Field as a TLV (Header ID, Data Size, Data)?\n3. **Header ID Usage**: Does it explain that Header IDs are used to identify different types of Extra Fields?\n4. **Multiple Extra Fields**: Does it mention that multiple Extra Fields can be added?\n5. **Versioning**: Does it discuss the version fields (version needed to extract, version made by)?\n6. **Handling Unknown Fields**: Does it explain that unknown fields are skipped by their size?\n7. **ZIP64 Support**: Does it mention ZIP64 and its role in extending the format?\n8. **Extensibility**: Does it discuss how the format allows for future extensions through these mechanisms?\n\nI need to ensure each criterion is specific to the prompt and can be evaluated as YES/NO. Also, avoid generic advice. Let me check if these are all covered in the reference and samples. Yes, all these points are covered. Now, I need to translate these into Korean, make sure they are binary, and structure them correctly in JSON.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 ZIP 헤더에서 확장 가능한 구조(Extra Field)를 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 Extra Field의 TLV 구조(Header ID, Data Size, Data)를 구체적으로 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 Header ID를 통해 다양한 확장 유형을 구분하는 메커니즘을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여러 개의 Extra Field가 포함될 수 있는 구조를 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 버전 필드(필요 버전, 생성 버전)를 통해 호환성을 관리하는 메커니즘을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 모르는 Extra Field는 Data Size로 건너뛰는 규칙을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 ZIP64 확장이 크기/오프셋 한계를 넘기도록 설계된 구조를 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 헤더의 확장성(Extra Field, 버전 필드, ZIP64)을 통해 미래 기능 추가를 가능하게 했음을 설명합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
