erials, and philosophical bases.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all cover symmetry (asymmetry vs. symmetry), space design (natural vs. geometric), philosophical aspects (Confucianism, Daoism, etc.), and cultural values. So the rubrics should be based on these elements.\n\nThe first rubric should be about following the instruction. The reference response and samples all address the required aspects, so a YES if they do, NO otherwise.\n\nNext, the second rubric could be about the depth of comparison. The samples go into detailed comparisons of each aspect, so checking if the response thoroughly compares both gardens on the specified points.\n\nThird, the response should mention both cultural aesthetics and values. The samples discuss how each garden reflects its culture, so a YES if both are addressed.\n\nFourth, the response should include specific examples of gardens. The samples mention specific examples like Cheonggyeong, Versailles, etc., so checking if examples are provided.\n\nFifth, the response should cover the philosophical underpinnings. The samples discuss Confucianism, Daoism, and Baroque philosophy, so a YES if these are included.\n\nSixth, the response should address the spatial design differences. The samples talk about natural vs. geometric space usage, so checking if this is covered.\n\nSeventh, the response should mention the use of materials and elements. The samples discuss materials like natural stones, plants, etc., so a YES if this is included.\n\nEighth, the response should ensure that the comparison is balanced and not biased. The samples present both gardens fairly, so checking if the response is balanced.\n\nI need to make sure each rubric is specific, binary, and not generic. Also, avoid copying text from the samples or reference. Now, structure these into 8 criteria with IDs, axes, importance, weight, and text in Korean.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 대칭성, 공간 사용, 철학적 근거를 중심으로 두 정원의 비교를 명확히 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"depth_of_comparison\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 정원의 설계 원리에 대한 세부적인 대비(예: 대칭성 유형, 공간 구성 방식)를 구체적으로 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_reflection\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 한국 정원과 프랑스 바로크 정원이 각각의 문화적 미학과 가치(예: 절제 vs. 권력 표상)를 어떻게 반영하는지 명확히 논의합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"specific_examples\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 창덕궁 후원, 베르사유 등 대표적인 사례를 구체적으로 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"philosophical_basis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 정원의 철학적 근거(예: 도가적 자연관, 데카르트적 합리주의)를 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"spatial_design\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 정원의 공간 사용 방식(예: 지형 순응 vs. 재단)과 동선 설계 차이를 구체적으로 비교합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"material_elements\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 물, 식재, 재료 사용(예: 자연석 vs. 토피어리)의 차이를 명확히 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"balance_and_objectivity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 정원의 장단점을 공정하게 비교하며, 문화적 차이를 중립적으로 논의합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
