{"prompt_id": "prompt_45771271fc76", "pair_id": "pair_263e1ea1ed3b", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:672bf2]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:c76c86]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:954b95]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:761a1b]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create 8 rubrics for evaluating the user's response to the query about the impact of Japanese colonial policies on Korean language policy and education. The rubrics should be binary (YES/NO) and specific to the prompt. Let me start by understanding the reference response and the sample responses to identify key aspects.\n\nFirst, the reference response mentions the Japanese policy of making Korean a secondary language, the suppression of Korean education, and the long-term effects on modern Korean. The sample responses elaborate on the historical stages, educational changes, and the lasting influence on vocabulary, grammar, and administrative language.\n\nSo, the main points to cover are: adherence to the instruction, historical accuracy, detailed analysis of different periods, impact on education, long-term effects on vocabulary, administrative language, standardization efforts, and the balance between suppression and resistance.\n\nLet me list possible rubrics:\n\n1. Instruction Followed: Does the response address the specific request about the impact of Japanese policies on Korean language and education?\n2. Historical Accuracy: Correctly identifies key periods and policies (e.g., 1910s, 1920s, 1930s).\n3. Detailed Analysis of Stages: Breaks down the policy changes into distinct phases.\n4. Impact on Education: Discusses how education was affected, including curriculum changes.\n5. Long-term Vocabulary Effects: Mentions the influence of Japanese-derived vocabulary on modern Korean.\n6. Administrative Language: Addresses the use of Japanese in administrative contexts.\n7. Standardization Efforts: References the Korean language standardization movements (e.g., 1933).\n8. Balance of Suppression and Resistance: Acknowledges both the suppression and the resistance efforts.\n\nNow, I need to ensure each rubric is specific and binary. Let me check if these cover the necessary aspects without being too vague. The reference response and samples do discuss these points, so these rubrics should work. Each should be a yes/no check based on whether the response includes that element.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일제 강점기의 한일 정치 관계가 한국어 정책과 교육에 미친 영향, 그리고 그 시기의 언어 정책이 현대 한국어에 남긴 장기적 영향을 분석하는 데 집중하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 1910년대 무단통치, 1920년대 문화통치, 1930년대 전시동화 등 시기별 언어 정책의 변화를 정확히 반영하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"stage_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 교육 정책의 단계적 변화(1911 조선교육령, 1938 교육령 개정 등)를 구체적으로 분석하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"educational_impact\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 학교 교육에서 일본어의 우위화, 조선어 과목 축소, 교원 양성 체계의 일본화 등 교육 현장의 변화를 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"vocabulary_influence\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일본어 경유 한자어(예: 사회, 경제, 철학)가 현대 한국어 어휘에 남은 장기적 영향을 구체적으로 언급하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"administrative_language\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일본어가 행정·법정·군사 영역에서 공용어로 강제된 사례(예: 창씨개명, 지명 일본식화)를 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"standardization_efforts\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 조선어학회의 한글 맞춤법 통일안, 1936 표준어 사정안 등 민간 주도의 표준화 운동을 언급하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"suppression_resistance_balance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일본어 강요와 한국어 보존 운동(예: 한글날 제정, 조선어학회 사건)의 역설적 관계를 분석하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
