{"prompt_id": "prompt_45771271fc76", "pair_id": "pair_2a9c26570e89", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:37e610]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:afb3a0]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:e49535]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:a38102]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's query about the impact of Japanese colonial policies on Korean language policy and education, and their long-term effects on modern Korean. The criteria must be binary (YES/NO) and specific to the prompt. Let me start by understanding the reference response and the sample responses to identify key aspects.\n\nFirst, the reference response discusses the suppression of Korean language, the introduction of Japanese as the official language, the changes in education curricula, and the long-term effects on modern Korean, including hybrid language use and the influence on current language policies. The sample responses also mention specific points like the stages of Japanese policy, the impact on education, the standardization efforts, and the lasting effects on vocabulary, grammar, and administrative language.\n\nSo, the main areas to cover are: adherence to the instruction (following the prompt), accuracy in historical context, depth of analysis on policy changes, impact on education, long-term effects on modern Korean, standardization efforts, cultural and identity aspects, and the use of specific terminology.\n\nLet me list possible criteria:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response address the specific request about the impact of Japanese policies on Korean language and education, and their long-term effects?\n2. Historical Accuracy: Correctly identifies the key periods and policies of Japanese colonization.\n3. Depth of Analysis: Thoroughly examines the changes in education and language policies.\n4. Long-term Effects: Clearly explains the lasting influence on modern Korean language.\n5. Standardization Efforts: Mentions the role of organizations like the Korean Language Society in standardizing the language.\n6. Cultural and Identity Aspects: Discusses the impact on Korean cultural identity and national consciousness.\n7. Terminology Use: Correctly uses terms like \"hybrid language\" and \"standardization.\"\n8. Structure and Clarity: Organizes the response logically, covering all required aspects without being vague.\n\nI need to ensure each criterion is specific and binary. Let me check if these are covered in the reference and samples. The reference response does mention the stages of Japanese policy, the impact on education, standardization efforts, and long-term effects. The samples also elaborate on these points. So, these criteria should be valid. Now, I'll structure them into JSON format as specified.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일제 강점기의 한일 정치 관계가 한국어 정책과 교육에 미친 영향, 그리고 그 시기의 언어 정책이 현대 한국어에 남긴 장기적 흔적을 분석하는 데 집중하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 1910년대 무단통치, 1920년대 문화통치, 1930년대 전시동화 등 일제 강점기의 단계별 정치·언어 정책을 정확히 반영하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"depth_of_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 교육 과정에서의 일본어 강제화, 한국어 사용의 억압, 그리고 학교 교과서·시험 체계의 변화를 구체적으로 분석하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"long_term_effects\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 현대 한국어의 어휘 구조, 문체, 표준어 정서법에 남은 일본 경유 한자어와 관료 문체의 영향을 명확히 설명하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"standardization_efforts\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 조선어학회의 1933년 한글 맞춤법 통일안, 1936년 표준어 사정안 등 민간 주도의 표준화 노력이 해방 후 정책에 영향을 미쳤음을 설명하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_identity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일본어 강요가 한국어 정체성 약화와 한글 전용 운동의 근본적 배경이 되었음을 강조하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"terminology_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '혼성 문해', '일본식 한자어', '관료 문체' 등의 전문 용어를 정확하게 사용하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure_and_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 정치·교육·언어학적 층위를 구분해 체계적으로 분석하고, 장기적 영향을 명확히 정리하고 있습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_a919985c7a4a", "pair_id": "pair_2a9fc3499d56", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:172a16]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:728e31]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:55421d]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:a21660]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's request about setting up a Site-to-Site VPN between two homes. The user provided a reference response and several sample responses. The criteria must be specific to the prompt, binary (YES/NO), and not generic.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It details hardware and software needed, including specific devices like Cisco ASA, Juniper SRX, Ubiquiti EdgeRouter, and mentions protocols like IPSec and WireGuard. The sample responses also vary, some using WireGuard, others IPsec, and mention different hardware like MikroTik, UniFi, and OpenWrt.\n\nThe key points from the reference are: hardware (VPN gateways), software (VPN management, encryption protocols), configuration examples, and testing. The samples include detailed steps, specific devices, and protocols.\n\nNow, I need to derive 8 criteria that are specific to the prompt. Let's brainstorm:\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response follow the user's instruction to suggest hardware and software for Site-to-Site VPN, including examples?\n2. **Hardware Recommendation**: Does the response include specific hardware suggestions (like routers, gateways)?\n3. **Software Recommendation**: Does it mention necessary software (like VPN management tools, encryption protocols)?\n4. **Protocol Specification**: Does it specify the protocol used (WireGuard, IPsec)?\n5. **Configuration Example**: Does it provide a concrete example of how to set up the VPN?\n6. **Network Design**: Does it address network design aspects like subnet allocation, IP addressing?\n7. **Testing and Validation**: Does it include steps for testing the setup?\n8. **DDNS or NAT Handling**: Does it address handling dynamic IP or NAT issues?\n\nNow, check if these are binary and specific. For example, \"Hardware Recommendation\" would be a YES if the response includes specific hardware, NO otherwise. Similarly for the others.\n\nI need to ensure each criterion is prompt-specific. For instance, \"Protocol Specification\" is about specifying the protocol, which is part of the user's request. Also, the criteria should not be generic advice but directly related to the task.\n\nNow, structure each criterion with the required fields. The reference response and samples all mention hardware, software, protocols, and examples, so these criteria should cover those aspects.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 사용자 요청에 따라 두 가정의 네트워크 장비 통신을 위한 Site-to-Site VPN의 소프트웨어/하드웨어 제안 및 예시 구성이 포함되어야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"hardware_recommendation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 구체적인 하드웨어(예: Ubiquiti EdgeRouter, MikroTik, OpenWrt 호환 라우터 등)를 제안해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"software_recommendation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 필요한 소프트웨어(예: WireGuard, IPsec, OpenWrt, pfSense 등)를 제안해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"protocol_specification\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 IPSec 또는 WireGuard와 같은 구체적인 프로토콜을 명시적으로 제안해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"configuration_example\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 구체적인 설정 예시(예: 라우터 구성, 터널 설정, 라우팅 규칙)를 포함해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"network_design\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 네트워크 설계 요소(예: 서브넷 배치, IP 주소 할당, NAT 처리)를 설명해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"testing_validation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 설정 검증 단계(예: 핑 테스트, 라우팅 확인, 서비스 검색)를 제안해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"ddns_nat_handling\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 동적 IP 또는 CGNAT 환경을 처리하는 방법(예: DDNS, VPS 중계)을 제안해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
