{"prompt_id": "prompt_94bbf07af45a", "pair_id": "pair_2f46186f3008", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:6a3fd5]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:315bbd]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:b965e7]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:0c2346]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, let's tackle this. The user wants me to create 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the question about what flies eat and whether mosquitoes only eat blood. The reference response and sample responses are detailed, so I need to extract the key points.\n\nFirst, I need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and can be judged as YES or NO. They should be binary and not vague. Let me look at the reference and samples.\n\nThe main points from the reference and samples are:\n- Flies eat various liquids, including fermented fruits, decayed matter, and animal secretions.\n- Mosquitoes don't just eat blood; females consume nectar or plant sap for energy, and only feed on blood for protein to lay eggs.\n- Mosquito larvae eat organic matter in water.\n- Different fly species have different diets, like fruit flies vs. flesh flies.\n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n1. Correctly states that flies eat liquids and decayed matter.\n2. Correctly explains that mosquitoes eat nectar/sap for energy.\n3. Mentions that female mosquitoes eat blood for eggs.\n4. Differentiates between fly species' diets.\n5. Correctly notes that mosquito larvae eat organic matter in water.\n6. Explains that not all mosquitoes eat blood (only females, and only when needed).\n7. Correctly identifies that flies eat a variety of substances.\n8. Clarifies that blood is not the main food source for mosquitoes.\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me check if these are all distinct and specific. Also, each should be a binary yes/no. Let me structure them properly.\n\nR1: Instruction Following - Does the response answer the question directly?\nR2: Accuracy - Correctly states that flies eat various liquids and decayed matter.\nR3: Specificity - Mentions different fly species' diets.\nR4: Clarification of Mosquito Diet - Explains that mosquitoes eat nectar/sap and blood for eggs.\nR5: Correctness of Mosquito Larvae Diet - States that larvae eat organic matter in water.\nR6: Differentiation of Mosquito Roles - Notes that only females eat blood.\nR7: Correctness of Blood as Main Food - States that blood is not the main food.\nR8: Comprehensive Coverage - Covers all key points without missing important info.\n\nWait, maybe some of these are overlapping. Let me ensure each is unique and specific. Also, the reference response mentions that mosquitoes don't just eat blood, and that they eat nectar. The samples also clarify that females eat blood for eggs. So, the criteria should reflect these points.\n\nI think that's 8. Now, I need to make sure each is a binary yes/no and not vague. Let me check each one again.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 모기와 파리의 식습관에 대한 질문에 직접적으로 답변합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"파리가 액체 또는 반액체 유기물(과즙, 썩은 음식물 등)을 먹는다는 사실을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"specificity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"파리의 종류별 식성(예: 과일파리, 검정파리)을 구분하여 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모기의 주식은 꽃꿀이나 식물 수액이지만, 암컷만 피를 빨아 알을 만드는 점을 명확히 합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모기 유충이 물속에서 미생물이나 유기물 찌꺼기를 먹는다는 사실을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"differentiation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모기의 성별별 식습관(수컷은 피를 안 먹고, 암컷은 피를 빨아 알을 만든다)을 구분하여 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"피는 모기의 주식이 아니며, 단백질 공급원으로만 사용된다는 점을 명확히 합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"comprehensiveness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모기와 파리의 식습관을 종류별로 구분하고, 생태계 내 역할(분해자, 번식자)을 설명합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_acba26bcd1e7", "pair_id": "pair_2f9d3a3c6bd8", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:0d494c]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:5c4329]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:058eba]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:78e253]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating responses to the user's query about the standards for assessing a country's economic situation. The user provided a reference response and several sample responses. The goal is to come up with 8 binary YES/NO criteria that are specific to the prompt and not too vague.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It lists several indicators like GDP growth, unemployment rate, investment rate, consumption rate, currency stability, debt ratio, and income inequality. The sample responses also mention similar indicators but with more detailed breakdowns, like using a dashboard approach with multiple axes such as growth, employment, inflation, fiscal health, and sustainability.\n\nThe key is to identify the core aspects that the reference and samples emphasize. The user wants the criteria to be specific to the prompt, so I need to focus on the main elements that the reference and samples discuss. The criteria should be binary, so each should be a yes/no question that can be answered based on whether the response includes the necessary elements.\n\nLooking at the samples, they all mention using a dashboard approach, considering multiple indicators, and balancing short-term and long-term factors. They also talk about factors like growth, employment, inflation, fiscal health, sustainability, and distribution. \n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n\n1. Does the response use a dashboard approach with multiple indicators?\n2. Does it include both short-term and long-term factors?\n3. Does it address economic stability (inflation, currency, debt)?\n4. Does it consider distribution and inequality?\n5. Does it mention sustainability and long-term growth?\n6. Does it include employment and labor market indicators?\n7. Does it cover fiscal health and government debt?\n8. Does it discuss the balance between growth and stability?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific and can be evaluated as a yes/no. Also, they should be in Korean as per the user's request. Let me check if these are all covered in the reference and samples. The reference lists GDP, unemployment, investment, consumption, currency, debt, and inequality. The samples expand on these with more detailed axes like growth, employment, inflation, fiscal health, sustainability, etc.\n\nSo, the criteria should be based on these elements. Let me structure them properly in JSON format with the required fields.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 경제 평가 기준의 다각적 접근을 제시하고, 단일 지표로 단정하지 않는 대시보드식 구조를 포함해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 단기 경기(성장, 고용, 물가)와 중장기 체력(생산성, 재정, 대외건전성)을 구분해 평가 기준을 제시해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 분배·포용성(소득 격차, 주거 부담, 생활수준)와 지속가능성(환경, 인적자본, 재정)을 함께 고려해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 경기(단기)와 구조(중장기)를 분리해, 단기 지표(성장, 고용, 물가)와 구조적 지표(생산성, 재정, 대외)를 구분해 평가해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 실질 지표(1인당 GDP, 실질임금)와 명목 지표(총 GDP, 임금)를 구분해 물가 조정과 PPP 기준을 반영해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 재정·대외건전성(정부부채, 경상수지, 외환보유액)과 금융안정성(부채 비율, 자산가격 과열)을 함께 평가해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 선행·동행·후행 지표(PMI, 소비자심리, 실업률)를 구분해 경기 변동성을 분석해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 국제비교 시 PPP 기준과 동일 시점·정의를 반영해 경제 상황의 현실성을 보장해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
