{"prompt_id": "prompt_7db5627ebdc8", "pair_id": "pair_305a371d491b", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:76baa3]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:292bc3]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:6159de]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:5a40be]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's query about Korea's low birth rate problem. The user provided a reference response and several sample responses. The criteria should be specific to the prompt, binary (YES/NO), and not vague.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It covers the current situation, causes, and proposed policies. The sample responses also include detailed analysis and specific policy packages. The key elements in the reference and samples are: analyzing the current situation, identifying causes, proposing innovative and feasible policies, and ensuring the policies are actionable.\n\nSo, the criteria should focus on whether the response addresses each of these aspects. Let me think of 8 specific points. \n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response address the user's request to analyze the current situation, causes, and propose policies? That's essential.\n\n2. **Comprehensive Analysis**: Does the response thoroughly analyze the current situation and causes? Important for understanding the problem.\n\n3. **Innovative Policies**: Are the proposed policies innovative and not just standard measures? This is crucial for the user's request.\n\n4. **Feasibility**: Are the policies practical and executable? The user wants actionable solutions.\n\n5. **Structure and Organization**: Is the response well-structured with clear sections (situation, causes, policies)? Good structure helps in evaluation.\n\n6. **Data and Evidence**: Does the response use data or references to support the analysis and policies? This adds credibility.\n\n7. **Clarity and Specificity**: Are the policies clearly defined and specific enough? Vague policies are not helpful.\n\n8. **Holistic Approach**: Does the response address multiple aspects (economic, social, structural) rather than isolated issues? A holistic approach is better.\n\nNow, I need to make sure each criterion is binary (YES/NO) and specific. Let me check if these criteria fit the reference and sample responses. The reference response includes all these elements, and the samples also have detailed analysis and specific policies. So, these criteria should work. Now, I'll format them into JSON as per the instructions.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 한국의 저출산 현황, 원인 분석, 혁신적 정책 제안을 모두 포함하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"comprehensive_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 현황·원인을 데이터나 구체적 사례로 구체적으로 분석하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"innovative_policies\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"제안된 정책이 기존 정책과 차별화된 혁신적 접근을 포함하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"feasibility\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"제안된 정책이 실행 가능성과 현실적 구현 경로를 명확히 제시하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure_organization\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답이 현황·원인·정책을 구조화된 단계로 나누어 설명하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"data_evidence\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답이 통계·사례·문제 진단을 바탕으로 한 구체적 근거를 제시하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"clarity_specificity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"제안된 정책이 구체적 실행 방안과 시간·비용·대상이 명확히 정의되어 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"holistic_approach\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답이 경제·사회·구조적 요인을 종합적으로 고려한 통합적 접근을 포함하고 있는가?\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_23677c128523", "pair_id": "pair_3075a666e5c8", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:24db77]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:f2678d]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:33edac]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:0fdb55]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's query about estimating the total agricultural production of the Korean Peninsula during the Imjin War (1592-1598). The user provided a reference response and several sample responses. The goal is to come up with 8 binary YES/NO criteria that are specific to the prompt and not vague.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It mentions that the war significantly reduced agricultural production, leading to a decrease in food supply and government efforts to increase production. However, it's a bit general. The sample responses are more detailed, providing specific numbers, calculations, and explanations about the methods used, like population estimates, per capita consumption, and the impact of the war on different years.\n\nThe key points from the samples are: using population data, per capita consumption, adjusting for losses, considering the war's impact on different years, and providing ranges with uncertainties. Also, the samples mention the use of units like stones and tons, and the conversion between them.\n\nSo, the criteria should focus on whether the response follows the instruction, provides specific numbers, uses appropriate units, accounts for the war's impact, includes uncertainty ranges, references historical data, explains the methodology, and considers regional variations.\n\nLet me list possible criteria:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response directly address the question about estimating the total agricultural production during the war?\n2. Specific Numerical Estimates: Does the response provide specific numbers or ranges for the total production?\n3. Unit Consistency: Does the response use consistent units (e.g., tons or stones) and explain the conversion?\n4. War Impact Consideration: Does the response account for the war's effect on production, such as reduced yields or losses?\n5. Uncertainty Range: Does the response include a range of possible values with an explanation of the uncertainty?\n6. Historical Data Reference: Does the response reference historical data or methods used for estimation?\n7. Methodology Explanation: Does the response explain the methods used to arrive at the estimate (e.g., population, per capita consumption)?\n8. Regional Variations: Does the response consider regional differences in the impact of the war on production?\n\nNow, I need to make sure each criterion is binary (YES/NO) and specific. The reference response might not have all these elements, but the samples do. For example, the reference response is general, while the samples provide detailed calculations and ranges.\n\nI should check if each criterion is met in the reference and samples. The reference response doesn't provide specific numbers or ranges, so \"Specific Numerical Estimates\" would be NO. The samples do have specific numbers and ranges, so that would be YES.\n\nSimilarly, the reference response doesn't explain the methodology, so \"Methodology Explanation\" would be NO. The samples do explain their methods, so YES.\n\nI need to ensure that each criterion is prompt-specific. For example, \"War Impact Consideration\" is relevant here because the question is about the war's effect on production.\n\nNow, translating these into the required JSON format with the correct structure and Korean text.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 임진왜란 기간 동안 한반도의 총 농업 생산량을 추정하는 직접적인 요청을 충족합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"numerical_estimation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 구체적인 수치(예: 톤 또는 석 단위)를 포함한 생산량 추정을 제공합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"unit_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 단위(예: 톤, 석)의 정의와 환산 방법을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"war_impact_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 전쟁의 직접적 영향(예: 경작지 파괴, 수확 감소)을 생산량 추정에 반영합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"uncertainty_range\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 추정치의 불확실성 범위(예: ±10~20%)를 명시적으로 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_reference\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 역사적 자료(예: 인구 통계, 조세 기록)를 근거로 생산량을 추정합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"methodology_explanation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 추정 방법(예: 인구 기반 접근, 전쟁 충격률 적용)을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"regional_variability\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 지역 간 생산량 차이(예: 남부 평야 vs. 북부 산간)를 고려합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
