lidation data to find optimal thresholds.\n- Calibration techniques (like Platt scaling).\n- Grid search over possible thresholds.\n- Class-wise thresholds.\n- Adaptive thresholds based on image-specific data.\n- Soft-NMS or WBF for reducing sensitivity to thresholds.\n- Using percentiles or top-K for online adjustments.\n- NMS IoU threshold optimization.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 binary criteria. Each criterion should check if the response addresses a specific aspect of the problem.\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response address finding an automatic method for threshold selection?\n2. **Validation Data Use**: Does it mention using a validation set for optimization?\n3. **Calibration Techniques**: Does it suggest methods like Platt scaling or temperature scaling?\n4. **Grid Search**: Does it propose a grid search over thresholds?\n5. **Class-wise Thresholds**: Does it mention handling different classes separately?\n6. **Adaptive Thresholds**: Does it suggest image-specific adjustments?\n7. **Soft-NMS/WBF**: Does it recommend techniques that reduce threshold sensitivity?\n8. **NMS IoU Optimization**: Does it address optimizing the NMS IoU threshold?\n\nEach of these should be a binary check. Now, I need to make sure each criterion is specific and not generic. For example, \"uses validation data\" is specific, while \"mentions calibration\" is also specific.\n\nI should avoid generic advice like \"good structure\" and focus on the specific aspects related to threshold optimization. Also, ensure that each criterion is a yes/no question based on the response's content.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 자동화된 임계값 찾기 방법을 구체적으로 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"validation_data_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 검증 세트를 활용한 임계값 최적화 과정을 제시합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"calibration_techniques\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 점수 보정(예: Platt scaling) 기법을 포함합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"grid_search\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 임계값 스윕(0.05~0.95) 및 최적화 방법을 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"class_wise_thresholds\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 클래스별 임계값 설정이 필요하다고 강조합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"adaptive_thresholds\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 이미지별 점수 분포 기반 자동 임계값 조정 방법을 제시합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"soft_nms_wbf\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 Soft-NMS 또는 WBF 기법을 포함합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"nms_iou_optimization\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 NMS IoU 임계값과의 상호작용을 고려한 최적화를 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
