{"prompt_id": "prompt_48e22489246c", "pair_id": "pair_38d2e00b1c05", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:e5c3d4]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:63ccff]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:336abf]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:9d1a13]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's request about the 3-tier architecture for a Java Spring application on AWS. The reference response and sample responses are provided, so I should base the criteria on what's important in those examples.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It lists each tier with specific AWS services and their purposes, then gives an example. The sample responses also have detailed explanations of each tier, including services like Route 53, CloudFront, WAF, ALB, ECS Fargate, RDS, ElastiCache, etc. \n\nThe user's request is about high availability, so the criteria should focus on whether the response correctly identifies the services for each tier and their purposes. Also, the example should be clear and practical.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all mention the three tiers: Presentation, Application, Data. Each tier has specific services. The key points are:\n\n1. Correct identification of services for each tier.\n2. Clear explanation of the purpose of each service.\n3. A practical example that demonstrates the architecture.\n4. Use of AWS services that support high availability.\n5. Proper use of security measures.\n6. Correct use of auto-scaling and load balancing.\n7. Proper configuration of networking and security groups.\n8. Integration of monitoring and observability tools.\n\nSo, the criteria should be binary (yes/no) and specific to the prompt. Let me list them:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response correctly identify the three tiers and their respective services?\n2. Tier-Specific Services: Does each tier have the correct AWS services listed?\n3. Purpose Explanation: Are the purposes of each service clearly explained?\n4. High Availability: Are services that support high availability (like Multi-AZ, Auto Scaling) included?\n5. Security Measures: Are security services (WAF, IAM, VPC) mentioned?\n6. Practical Example: Does the response provide a concrete example of the architecture?\n7. Networking Configuration: Are VPC, subnets, and security groups properly described?\n8. Monitoring and Observability: Are tools like CloudWatch, X-Ray, and WAF included?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and not generic. Also, the criteria should be in Korean as per the user's request. Let me structure them in JSON with the required fields.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"3-tier 구조(프론트엔드, 애플리케이션, 데이터베이스)를 명확히 정의하고 각 계층의 용도를 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"service_specificity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 계층에 적절한 AWS 서비스(예: ALB, RDS, ElastiCache)를 구체적으로 제시하고 그 목적을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"high_availability\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"고가용성을 지원하는 서비스(예: Multi-AZ, Auto Scaling, Read Replica)를 포함하고 장애 대응 전략을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"security_measures\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"보안 관련 서비스(예: WAF, IAM, VPC 보안 그룹)를 포함하고 데이터 암호화, 접근 제어를 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"practical_example\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"구체적인 예시(예: 프론트엔드 캐시, 애플리케이션 로드 밸런싱, 데이터베이스 백업)를 제공하고 요청 흐름을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"networking_config\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"VPC, 서브넷 분리, 네트워크 보안 그룹, NAT 게이트웨이 등 네트워크 설계를 명확히 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"observability\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모니터링(예: CloudWatch, X-Ray), 로그 수집, 트레이싱 도구를 포함하고 장애 감지 메커니즘을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"deployment_practices\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"CI/CD 파이프라인(예: CodePipeline, CodeDeploy), 자동화된 배포 전략(예: Blue/Green)을 포함하고 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
