portant, so weight 0.3.\n\nThen, the calculation method. The reference uses population divided by area, so checking if the formula is correctly applied. That's essential, weight 0.3.\n\nAccuracy of the numbers is important. The reference uses 2022 data, so the answer should include the correct year. That's essential, weight 0.2.\n\nThe answer should explain the calculation steps. The reference shows the division, so checking if the steps are explained. Weight 0.2.\n\nClarity of the explanation. The reference is clear, so if the answer is concise and to the point, that's a criterion. Weight 0.1.\n\nUnits are mentioned in the reference, so checking if the units (per km²) are included. Weight 0.1.\n\nFinally, the answer should be self-contained, not relying on external sources. The reference doesn't mention any, so checking if the answer is self-contained. Weight 0.1.\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me make sure each is binary and specific. Maybe adjust the weights to sum up to 1. Let me check again. The reference response has 8 criteria, each with different weights. Need to ensure each is prompt-specific and binary. Also, avoid vague advice. The criteria should be about whether the answer includes specific elements, not general advice. So the 8 criteria are: ratio, both densities, calculation method, correct year, steps, clarity, units, self-contained. That's 8. Each is a yes/no. That should work.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 서울 인구 밀도가 부산의 약 3.6배임을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"data_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"서울과 부산의 인구 밀도 계산에 사용된 데이터는 2022년 행정안전부 통계 기준을 반영합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"methodology\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"인구 밀도 계산에 '인구/면적'의 수학적 공식을 올바르게 적용합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"numerical_precision\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"서울 인구 밀도 15,849.26명/km²와 부산 4,397.03명/km²의 계산값을 정확히 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"explanation_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"계산 과정을 단계별로 명확히 설명하여 결과의 신뢰성을 보장합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"unit_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"인구 밀도 계산값이 '명/km²' 단위로 일관되게 표현됩니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"contextual_relevance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"연도와 통계 기준이 명시되어 결과의 타당성을 강화합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"self_containment\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"외부 데이터나 참고 자료를 의존하지 않고 독자적으로 계산하여 결과를 제시합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
