nformative, like mentioning financial checks, while others are more poetic. The reference response is more about the season and a friendly closing. The samples vary in how they incorporate the seasonal aspect and the closing line.\n\nSo, the criteria need to be specific. Let's think about what's essential. The user wants each month's text to have three sentences, a seasonal reference, and a closing line. Also, the reference response uses a specific closing line, so that's important.\n\nFirst criterion: Instruction following. Check if each response has three sentences and a closing line. The reference does that, so the rubric should check if each response meets that.\n\nSecond: Seasonal appropriateness. Each month should reflect the season. September is autumn, December winter, February spring. The reference uses autumn, winter, and spring references. So check if each response correctly reflects the season.\n\nThird: Closing line. The reference uses \"감사합니다.\" So check if each response ends with that.\n\nFourth: Tone and friendliness. The reference is friendly and welcoming. The samples vary, but the reference is more positive. So check if the tone is appropriate.\n\nFifth: Specificity to the bank's context. The reference mentions the bank's services, like checking balances, security. The samples have different approaches. So check if the response is relevant to banking.\n\nSixth: Length and structure. Each response should be exactly three sentences. The reference has three sentences each. Check if each response is three sentences.\n\nSeventh: Cultural appropriateness. The reference uses Korean seasonal terms and closing lines. Check if the samples use appropriate cultural references.\n\nEighth: Consistency across months. Each month's text should be distinct but follow the same structure. The reference has different seasonal references, so check if each month's text is unique but follows the structure.\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me list them again:\n\n1. Instruction Following (3 sentences, closing line)\n2. Seasonal Appropriateness (correct season for each month)\n3. Closing Line (specific closing)\n4. Tone and Friendliness (positive, welcoming)\n5. Relevance to Banking Context (mentions bank services)\n6. Sentence Structure (exactly three sentences)\n7. Cultural Appropriateness (correct Korean terms)\n8. Consistency Across Months (each month's text is distinct but follows structure)\n\nBut the user said the criteria should be binary (yes/no) and prompt-specific. Also, avoid generic advice. So each criterion should be a yes/no check based on the response.\n\nNow, I need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt. For example, \"Seasonal Appropriateness\" checks if each month's text correctly reflects the season. \"Closing Line\" checks if the exact closing line is used.\n\nI think that's it. Now, structure them into JSON with the required fields.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 월별 응답이 3문장으로 구성되고 마지막 문장에 끝인사가 포함되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"seasonal_appropriateness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"9월은 가을, 12월은 겨울, 2월은 봄의 계절감이 명확히 반영되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"closing_line\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"마지막 문장이 '감사합니다'로 끝나는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"tone_and_friendliness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답의 어조가 친절하고 환영하는 메시지로 구성되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"banking_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"은행 서비스와 관련된 언급(예: 자동이체, 보안설정 등)이 포함되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"sentence_structure\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 응답이 정확히 3문장으로 구성되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_appropriateness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"한국 문화적 맥락(예: 추석, 설 연휴)에 맞는 언급이 포함되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"consistency_across_months\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 월별 응답이 계절별로 구분되며, 구조적 일관성이 있는가?\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
