 reference response and several sample responses. My task is to extract the key points from these and form 8 binary criteria (YES/NO) that are specific to the prompt and not too vague.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It mentions three main points: the condition must be boolean, both values must have compatible types, and TypeScript infers the type based on the values. The samples expand on these points with more examples and additional rules like best common supertype, union types, contextual typing, narrowing, and handling of never, null/undefined, etc.\n\nNow, I need to identify the core aspects that are essential for a correct answer. The user's question is about the conditions under which the type of a ternary operator is determined. The reference and samples discuss several key factors:\n\n1. The condition must be a boolean.\n2. Both branches must have compatible types (best common supertype or union).\n3. Contextual typing (like variable declarations or function parameters) affects the inferred type.\n4. Literal types are preserved with 'as const' or in const contexts.\n5. Handling of 'never' in one branch.\n6. Null/undefined handling with strictNullChecks.\n7. Type narrowing within branches.\n8. Structural compatibility between objects or arrays.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific to the question and can be evaluated as YES/NO. Let's list possible criteria:\n\n1. Does the response correctly state that the condition must be a boolean?\n2. Does it explain that the types of both branches must be compatible (best common supertype or union)?\n3. Does it mention the role of contextual typing (like variable declarations or function parameters) in determining the type?\n4. Does it address the preservation of literal types using 'as const' or const contexts?\n5. Does it cover the handling of 'never' in one branch?\n6. Does it discuss null/undefined handling with strictNullChecks?\n7. Does it explain type narrowing within the branches?\n8. Does it mention structural compatibility between objects or arrays?\n\nNow, I need to check if these are all covered in the reference and samples. The reference response does mention the condition being boolean, and the samples elaborate on the best common supertype, contextual typing, literal preservation, never, null/undefined, narrowing, and structural compatibility.\n\nEach of these can be a separate criterion. Now, I need to phrase them in Korean as binary criteria, ensuring they are specific and not generic. Also, each should be a separate object in the JSON array with the required fields.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 삼항 연산자의 조건식이 boolean 타입이어야 한다고 명시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 분기의 타입이 동일하거나 공통 상위 타입을 가져야 한다고 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 문맥적 타이핑(변수 선언, 함수 인자 등)이 결과 타입 결정에 영향을 미친다고 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 리터럴 타입을 유지하기 위해 'as const' 또는 const 문맥을 사용해야 한다고 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 한 분기가 'never'일 경우 결과 타입이 다른 분기의 타입이 된다고 명시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 strictNullChecks에서 null/undefined가 분기에 포함되면 유니온 타입이 된다고 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 분기 내부에서 타입 가드로 인해 타입이 좁혀지지만, 결과 타입은 두 분기의 유니언/공통 상위 타입이 된다고 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 객체/배열 분기의 구조적 호환성(공통 속성, 유니온 축약)을 결과 타입 결정에 반영한다고 설명합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_a1c35497f340", "pair_id": "pair_466b792eef52", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:cb7b5a]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:39cae5]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:0fb69b]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:7c02f8]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's request. The user asked to imagine a dialogue between Joseon-era scholars and write it as a script. The reference response is a sample dialogue, and there are several sample responses provided.\n\nFirst, I should look at the reference response and the sample responses to identify what makes a good response. The reference response has a structured dialogue with characters, setting, and a natural flow. The sample responses are more elaborate, with detailed scenes, character interactions, and specific topics like land distribution, trade, and technology.\n\nThe criteria need to be specific, binary (yes/no), and related to the task. They should not be vague. Let me think about the key aspects of a good script for this scenario.\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response follow the user's instruction to write a dialogue between Joseon scholars? The reference response does this, so this should be a key criterion.\n\n2. **Historical Accuracy**: Are the characters and their ideas historically accurate? The sample responses mention real scholars like Jeong Do-jeon, Park Jeong-hyeon, etc., so this is important.\n\n3. **Dialogue Flow**: Is the dialogue natural and coherent? The reference response has a flow, but some samples might have more complex interactions.\n\n4. **Character Consistency**: Do the characters stay true to their historical roles and personalities? The samples have distinct characters with specific traits.\n\n5. **Content Relevance**: Does the dialogue cover relevant topics like land reform, trade, technology? The samples discuss these, so this is a key point.\n\n6. **Setting Description**: Is the setting well-described and appropriate? The reference response has a setting, but some samples are more detailed.\n\n7. **Use of Historical Context**: Does the dialogue incorporate historical context and references? The samples use terms and concepts from Joseon-era scholarship.\n\n8. **Cohesion and Structure**: Is the dialogue well-structured with clear scenes and transitions? The reference response has scenes, but some samples have more complex structures.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 binary criteria. Let me check if these are specific enough and not too generic. For example, \"Historical Accuracy\" is specific. \"Dialogue Flow\" is about the naturalness. \"Character Consistency\" ensures characters are consistent. \"Content Relevance\" covers the topics. \"Setting Description\" is about the setting. \"Use of Historical Context\" is about incorporating historical elements. \"Cohesion and Structure\" is about the overall structure.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is clear and can be evaluated as yes/no. Also, the criteria should be in Korean as per the user's request. Let me structure them accordingly.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 조선 시대 실학자들의 대화를 스크립트 형식으로 구체적으로 묘사했는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답에 조선 시대 실학자들의 사상, 역할, 대화 스타일이 역사적으로 정확하게 반영되었는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"dialogue_flow\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"대화가 자연스럽고 논리적으로 흐르며, 인물 간 상호작용이 명확히 표현되었는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"character_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 인물의 역할, 성격, 대화 방식이 역사적 배경에 맞게 일관되게 유지되었는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"content_relevance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"대화 내용이 조선 시대 실학자의 주요 관심사(토지 개혁, 상업, 기술 등)와 관련되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"setting_description\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"장소, 시간, 기후 등 배경이 구체적으로 묘사되어 있는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"대화에 조선 시대의 사회 구조, 철학적 이념, 기술적 배경이 자연스럽게 반영되었는가?\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"cohesion_structure\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"스크립트가 장면별로 구조화되어 있고, 전반적인 흐름이 명확히 유지되었는가?\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
