like using small formats, household crafts, symbolic motifs, and the use of anonymity.\n\nSo, the key points from the reference and samples are: \n- Use of small formats (like albums, fans, embroidery)\n- Symbolic motifs (flowers, insects, nature)\n- Anonymity and lack of formal recognition\n- Incorporation of natural elements to express inner emotions\n- Use of household crafts as a medium\n- Subtle resistance through symbolism and form\n- Themes of isolation and inner turmoil\n- The balance between conformity and individual expression\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 specific, binary criteria. Let me think of each criterion:\n\n1. **Use of Small Formats**: Did the response mention using small formats like albums or fans as a way to express constraints?\n2. **Symbolic Motifs**: Did the response use symbols like flowers, insects, or nature to represent inner emotions?\n3. **Anonymity**: Did the response discuss the use of anonymity or lack of formal recognition?\n4. **Household Crafts**: Did the response mention using household crafts like embroidery or ceramics as a medium?\n5. **Natural Elements**: Did the response incorporate natural elements to express inner feelings or societal constraints?\n6. **Subtle Resistance**: Did the response show subtle resistance through symbolism or form?\n7. **Themes of Isolation**: Did the response address themes of isolation or inner turmoil?\n8. **Conformity vs. Individual Expression**: Did the response balance conformity with individual expression?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and can be evaluated as YES or NO. Also, avoid generic advice. Let me check if these criteria cover the key aspects from the reference and samples. Yes, they seem to. Now, structure them into JSON with the required fields.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 조선 여성 예술가의 사회적 제약 속에서의 좌절과 도전을 예술적 형식과 상징으로 명확히 드러냈습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 소형 매체(앨범, 부채 그림, 자수)를 통해 여성 예술가의 사적 공간과 제약을 구체적으로 설명했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 자연 소재(초충, 포도, 나비)를 통해 여성의 내면적 욕망과 억압을 은유적으로 표현했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 익명성과 가명 사용을 통해 여성 예술가의 사회적 제약을 회피하고 자율성을 유지했다는 점을 명확히 했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성 예술가가 가정 내 공예(보자기, 자수)를 통해 예술적 실험을 수행했다는 점을 구체적으로 설명했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성 예술가의 좌절을 표현하기 위해 상징적 도상(길상문, 십장생)과 형식적 실험을 결합했다는 점을 명확히 했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성 예술가의 고립감과 내면적 힘을 표현하기 위해 감정적이고 미시적 세계를 강조했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 여성 예술가가 사회적 제약 속에서도 예술적 주체성을 유지하며, 제약을 미학적 전략으로 변환했다는 점을 구체적으로 설명했습니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
