\nLooking at the samples, they talk about genetic similarity, domestication-related changes, specific genes involved in digestion, social behavior, morphology, and regulatory elements. Also, the reference response mentions that dogs and wolves are closely related but have some differences in their genomes.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary and directly related to the genetic differences. Let's brainstorm possible criteria:\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response address the genetic differences between dogs and wolves? The reference and samples all do this, so this is essential.\n\n2. **Genetic Similarity**: Does the response mention that dogs and wolves are genetically very similar? The reference and samples do, so this is important.\n\n3. **Domestication Signals**: Does the response discuss genetic changes due to domestication, like CNVs or regulatory elements? The samples do this.\n\n4. **Specific Genes Involved**: Does the response mention specific genes like AMY2B, GTF2I, etc.? The samples do.\n\n5. **Morphological Differences**: Does the response talk about physical differences like size, fur, or body shape? The reference and samples do.\n\n6. **Behavioral/ Social Traits**: Does the response address social behavior changes, like increased sociability in dogs? The samples do.\n\n7. **Regulatory Elements**: Does the response mention regulatory regions or epigenetic factors? Some samples do.\n\n8. **Evolutionary Timeline**: Does the response include information about when domestication occurred? The reference and samples mention this.\n\nNow, I need to ensure each criterion is specific and binary. Let me check if these are all covered and not overlapping. Also, avoid generic advice. The criteria should be about the content of the response, not the writing style.\n\nI think these eight criteria cover the key aspects. Now, I'll structure them into JSON format as per the user's instructions.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 개와 늑대의 유전학적 차이점에 대해 명확히 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"genetic_similarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 개와 늑대가 유전적으로 매우 가까운 점을 강조합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"domestication_signals\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 가축화 과정에서 발생한 유전자 변이(예: CNV, 조절 영역 변화)를 언급합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"specific_genes\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 AMY2B, GTF2I, WBSCR 등 특정 유전자와 그 기능을 명시합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"morphological_differences\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 체구, 털, 두개안면 형태 등 외모 차이를 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"behavioral_traits\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 사회성, 공포 감소 등 행동적 차이를 유전학적으로 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"regulatory_elements\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 유전자 조절 영역(예: 인핸서, 복제수 변이)의 변화를 언급합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"evolutionary_timeline\",\n      \"importance\"