each paragraph starts with a topic, then elaborates. The samples also follow this pattern. So, another rubric could be about the structure of paragraphs, ensuring each has a clear topic sentence followed by details.\n\nThe reference response uses vivid imagery and descriptive language. The samples also use rich descriptions. So, a rubric about the use of vivid imagery and descriptive language would be important.\n\nThe user's prompt mentions introducing cultural aspects and attractions. The reference and samples include both, so a rubric to check if both are covered would be necessary.\n\nThe reference response has a cohesive flow, moving from one attraction to another. The samples also maintain a smooth flow. So, a rubric on coherence and flow would be essential.\n\nThe reference response uses a consistent tone, friendly and engaging. The samples also maintain this. So, a rubric on tone and style would be important.\n\nThe reference response is well-organized, with each paragraph focusing on a single idea. The samples follow this. So, a rubric on organization and focus would be needed.\n\nLastly, the reference response is concise and to the point, avoiding unnecessary details. The samples also do this. So, a rubric on conciseness and clarity would be essential.\n\nNow, I need to make sure each rubric is binary (YES/NO) and specific. Let me list them out:\n\n1. Each sentence starts with '가' – essential, high weight.\n2. Paragraph structure with topic sentence and details – essential.\n3. Vivid imagery and descriptive language – essential.\n4. Covers both cultural aspects and attractions – essential.\n5. Cohesive flow between paragraphs – essential.\n6. Consistent tone and style – essential.\n7. Clear organization of ideas – essential.\n8. Concise and clear expression – essential.\n\nI need to check if these are all specific to the prompt and not too vague. The reference and samples all follow these aspects, so the rubrics should align with that. Each rubric should be a yes/no check. I'll format them into JSON as specified.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모든 문장의 첫 글자가 '가'로 시작됨\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 섹션별 주제 문장과 세부 설명이 명확히 구분됨\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"descriptive_quality\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"풍경, 문화, 체험에 대한 생동감 있는 묘사 사용\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"content_coverage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"하와이의 문화적 요소와 명소가 모두 포함됨\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"coherence\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"문장 간 논리적 연결이 자연스럽게 유지됨\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"tone\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"친근하고 여행을 즐기는 태도가 일관되게 유지됨\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"organization\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 섹션의 주제가 명확히 구분되고 순서가 논리적임\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"문장이 간결하고 정보 전달이 명확하게 이루어짐\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_acaa09b5fe01", "pair_id": "pair_56b446d42ce4", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:dad9fd]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:593a0c]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:d496a3]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:8d369f]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a recursive rubric designer for LLM-as-a-judge. The user provided a query about comparing PyTorch and TensorFlow, along with a reference response and several sample responses. My task is to come up with 8 specific, binary criteria (YES/NO) that evaluate the quality of responses to this query. The criteria should be based on the reference response and the sample responses, avoiding vague advice.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It has a structured comparison table with various points like flexibility, learning curve, community support, etc. The recommendation section also gives clear guidelines. The sample responses are more detailed, covering aspects like research-friendly, deployment options, TPU support, and enterprise use cases.\n\nI need to identify key aspects that are critical for a good answer to the user's query. The user wants a comparison of strengths and weaknesses and a recommendation. So, the criteria should focus on whether the response covers these elements.\n\nLooking at the reference response, the main points are: clear comparison of features, accurate information on strengths and weaknesses, a clear recommendation, and structured formatting. The sample responses add more depth, like specific use cases, TPU support, and deployment options.\n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response directly address the user's request to compare PyTorch and TensorFlow and provide a recommendation?\n2. Comprehensive Comparison: Does the response cover all key aspects (flexibility, learning curve, community, etc.)?\n3. Accuracy of Information: Are the strengths and weaknesses correctly stated?\n4. Clear Recommendation: Does the response provide a clear, situation-based recommendation?\n5. Structured Formatting: Is the information presented in a clear, organized manner (tables, bullet points)?\n6. Specific Use Cases: Does the response mention specific scenarios where one library is better?\n7. TPU/Deployment Support: Does the response cover TPU support and deployment options?\n8. Enterprise/Research Focus: Does the response address both enterprise and research use cases?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary (YES/NO) and specific to the prompt. Also, avoid generic advice. Let me check if these criteria are covered in the reference and samples. The reference has a table and a recommendation. The samples go into more detail on specific use cases, TPU, deployment, etc.\n\nAnother point is whether the response includes both libraries' strengths and weaknesses. Also, the recommendation should be based on the comparison. So, maybe include a criterion on whether the recommendation is situation-based.\n\nI think these 8 criteria cover the essential aspects. Now, I need to translate them into Korean, ensuring they are specific and binary. Also, check that they are not vague. For example, \"Comprehensive Comparison\" would be a yes if the response includes all key points from the reference and samples.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is unique and not overlapping. Let me finalize the list.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 PyTorch와 TensorFlow의 장단점 비교 및 추천을 명확히 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"comprehensive_comparison\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 유연성, 학습 곡선, 커뮤니티, 메모리 관리 등 핵심 차이점을 모두 다룹니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 라이브러리의 장단점이 실제 사용 사례와 일치합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"clear_recommendation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 초보자/연구자 vs 대규모 프로덕션/TPU 지원 등 상황별 추천을 구체적으로 제공합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"structured_formatting\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 표, 목록, 구조화된 문단으로 정보를 체계적으로 전달합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"specific_use_cases\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 모바일/엣지 배포, TPU 지원, 엔터프라이즈 파이프라인 등 특정 시나리오를 다룹니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"deployment_support\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 TorchScript, TF Lite, TFLite Micro 등 배포 옵션을 비교합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"research_enterprise_balance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 연구/프로토타이핑과 대규모 프로덕션, 엔터프라이즈 요구사항을 모두 고려합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
