 be self-contained and correct.\n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n\n1. Uses three different HTTP libraries (requests, http.client, urllib). Each example must use a different one. So, check if all three are present.\n\n2. Each example correctly makes an HTTP POST request. Need to ensure that each code snippet uses POST method.\n\n3. JSON format is used in the payload and response. Check if data is serialized as JSON and the response is parsed as JSON.\n\n4. Each example is self-contained, meaning all necessary imports and code are included without external dependencies.\n\n5. Correct handling of headers, especially Content-Type: application/json. The samples show that some libraries automatically set this, others require manual setup.\n\n6. Proper error handling or timeout settings. Some examples include try-except blocks or timeout parameters.\n\n7. Correctly uses the libraries' specific methods. For example, requests uses json=, http.client uses request and getresponse, urllib uses Request and urlopen.\n\n8. The code examples are correctly formatted with proper indentation and syntax. Ensuring that the code is syntactically correct.\n\nWait, but the user said 8 criteria. Let me check again. The reference response includes three examples with different libraries, each with correct POST, JSON, and proper headers. The samples also vary in how they handle headers and error handling.\n\nSo, the criteria should cover:\n\n- All three libraries are used (requests, http.client, urllib)\n- Each example is a POST request\n- JSON data is used in payload and response\n- Correct headers (Content-Type: application/json)\n- Self-contained code\n- Proper error handling or timeout\n- Correct library-specific methods\n- Correct syntax and formatting\n\nBut need to make sure each is a binary yes/no. Let me structure them properly.\n\nR1: Uses three different HTTP libraries (requests, http.client, urllib). Check if all three are present.\n\nR2: Each example is a POST request. Check if each code snippet uses POST.\n\nR3: JSON data is used in the payload and response. Check if data is serialized as JSON and response is parsed.\n\nR4: Correct Content-Type header is set. Check if headers include Content-Type: application/json.\n\nR5: Code is self-contained. Check if all necessary imports and code are included.\n\nR6: Error handling or timeout is included. Check if try-except blocks or timeout parameters are present.\n\nR7: Correct library-specific methods are used. Check if each library's specific functions are used correctly.\n\nR8: Code is properly formatted with correct syntax. Check for syntax errors or formatting issues.\n\nThat's eight criteria. Now, translate these into Korean, ensuring they are specific and binary. Also, make sure they don't copy any text from reference or samples. Each criterion should be a clear yes/no check.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 requests, http.client, urllib 세 가지 라이브러리를 모두 사용한 예시가 포함되어 있습니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 예시 코드는 HTTP POST 요청을 명시적으로 수행하는 코드가 포함되어 있습니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모든 예시는 JSON 형식의 요청 본문과 응답을 처리하는 코드가 포함되어 있습니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"모든 예시는 Content-Type: application/json 헤더가 명시적으로 설정되어 있습니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"code_quality\",\