aning, model training, evaluation metrics, deployment, handling domain-specific data, and style control (formality).\n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response follow the user's instruction to build a translation model?\n2. Data Collection Mention: Does it mention collecting parallel corpora?\n3. Preprocessing Steps: Does it include data cleaning and normalization?\n4. Model Selection: Does it suggest using pre-trained models like M2M100 or NLLB?\n5. Training Process: Does it outline the training steps?\n6. Evaluation Metrics: Does it mention BLEU, METEOR, etc.?\n7. Deployment Strategy: Does it talk about deployment and API building?\n8. Domain Adaptation: Does it address adapting to specific domains?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary (YES/NO) and specific. Let me check if these are covered in the samples. The samples all mention data collection, pre-processing, model selection, training, evaluation, deployment, and domain adaptation. So these criteria should be valid.\n\nNow, I need to structure each criterion with the correct ID, axis, importance, weight, and text in Korean. The reference response and samples all cover these aspects, so each criterion should be YES if the response includes that element.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일본어에서 한국어로 번역하는 모델 구축을 위한 단계별 접근법을 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"data_collection\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 공개된 병렬 코퍼스와 자체 데이터 수집 방법을 구체적으로 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"preprocessing\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 데이터 정제(언어 