 the instruction (listing different types of food), providing specific details (names, addresses, prices), including wait times, offering variety, being concise, including tips, and being accurate (correct addresses and menu items).\n\nSo, the criteria should be binary (yes/no) and specific to the task. Let me think of 8 criteria:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response list different types of food and their specific places?\n2. Specific Details: Are there specific names, addresses, and prices provided?\n3. Wait Time Information: Does it mention wait times or suggest avoiding peak hours?\n4. Variety of Options: Are multiple types of food and cuisines covered?\n5. Conciseness: Is the information presented clearly without unnecessary details?\n6. Accuracy: Are the addresses and menu items correct?\n7. Tips or Additional Advice: Does it include helpful tips like visiting times or alternatives?\n8. Structure and Clarity: Is the response well-organized and easy to follow?\n\nWait, but the user said to avoid vague or generic advice. So maybe some of these can be combined or adjusted. Also, the reference response includes a variety of cuisines, specific details, and tips. The samples also have similar elements.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific and binary. Let me check again. For example, \"Instruction Following\" is essential. \"Specific Details\" would check if the response includes names, addresses, prices. \"Wait Time Information\" would check if it mentions wait times or peak hours. \"Variety of Options\" would check if multiple types of food are covered. \"Conciseness\" is about not being too wordy. \"Accuracy\" is about correct info. \"Tips\" would be if it includes advice. \"Structure and Clarity\" is about organization.\n\nBut maybe some of these can be merged. Let me ensure each is distinct and binary. Also, the reference response and samples have different structures, so the criteria should be based on what's important for the task. The user wants the rubric to be specific to the prompt, so the criteria should be about the structure and content of the response, not general writing advice.\n\nSo, the final 8 criteria would be:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Lists different types of food and their specific places.\n2. Specific Details: Includes names, addresses, prices.\n3. Wait Time Information: Mentions wait times or peak hours.\n4. Variety of Options: Covers multiple cuisines and food types.\n5. Conciseness: Information is clear and not verbose.\n6. Accuracy: Correct addresses and menu items.\n7. Tips or Additional Advice: Includes helpful tips like visiting times.\n8. Structure and Clarity: Well-organized and easy to follow.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into Korean, assign importance and weight, and make sure they are binary. The reference response and samples have these elements, so the criteria should reflect that.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 다양한 음식 종류(쌀국수, 브런치, 버거 등)를 구분하여 추천합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"specific_details\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 메뉴에 음식점 이름, 주소, 대표 메뉴, 가격대를 구체적으로 제공합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"wait_time_info\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"대기 시간, 피크 시간 피하는 방법 등 실용적인 정보를 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"variety_of_options\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"한국 음식, 외국 음식, 브런치, 버거 등 다양한 분야의 메뉴를 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"conciseness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"정보가 명확하고 지나치게 길지 않으며, 구조가 직관적입니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"주소, 메뉴, 가격 등 실제 존재하는 음식점 정보를 정확히 제공합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"tips\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"분위기, 예산, 대기 시간 등 사용자에게 유용한 팁을 추가로 포함합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"각 항목이 구분되어 있고, 읽기 쉬운 형식으로 구성되어 있습니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
