{"prompt_id": "prompt_0061cf483bb2", "pair_id": "pair_82a4b5e02ae0", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:be016c]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:6799f8]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:0915fd]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:f8c63e]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's query about how Korea's unique seasons affect the taste of kimchi, doenjang, and other fermented foods. The reference response and sample responses are provided, so I should analyze them to identify key aspects.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response. It talks about the traditional fermentation processes, the role of seasons in the fermentation, specific ingredients like gochujang, and how different seasons affect the microbial activity and the final taste. The sample responses also mention factors like temperature, humidity, microbial succession, and the use of specific tools like gogukjang (a type of fermentation vessel).\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all discuss how seasons influence the fermentation process, the types of microorganisms involved, the timing of fermentation, the use of specific ingredients, and the resulting taste and texture. For example, one sample mentions the effect of temperature on microbial activity, another talks about the role of humidity and the use of gogukjang, and another discusses the seasonal variations in the ingredients used.\n\nI need to extract 8 binary criteria that are specific to the prompt. Each criterion should be a yes/no question that can be evaluated based on whether the response addresses the key points. The criteria should be based on the reference and samples, avoiding vague advice.\n\nPossible criteria could include:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Whether the response accurately follows the user's instruction to analyze the impact of seasons on the taste of fermented foods.\n2. Seasonal Impact on Fermentation: Whether the response discusses how different seasons affect the fermentation process.\n3. Microbial Succession: Whether the response mentions the change in microbial communities during different seasons.\n4. Use of Traditional Tools: Whether the response references traditional fermentation tools like gogukjang.\n5. Ingredient Seasonality: Whether the response discusses how seasonal ingredients affect the taste.\n6. Temperature and Humidity Effects: Whether the response addresses the role of temperature and humidity in fermentation.\n7. Resulting Taste and Texture: Whether the response explains how seasons influence the final taste and texture of the foods.\n8. Cultural Context: Whether the response incorporates the cultural significance of seasons in fermentation practices.\n\nI need to ensure each criterion is specific, binary, and directly related to the user's query. The criteria should be derived from the reference and sample responses, not just general advice. Also, each criterion should be in Korean as per the user's request.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 한국의 계절이 김치, 된장의 발효 과정과 맛에 미치는 영향을 분석하는 데 집중하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"seasonal_impact_on_fermentation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 겨울, 여름, 봄·가을의 기후 조건이 발효 속도와 미생물 군집에 미치는 영향을 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"microbial_succession\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 계절별로 달라지는 미생물 천이(예: Leuconostoc → Lactobacillus)와 그에 따른 맛 변화를 다루고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"traditional_tools_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 옹기, 장독대, 땅속 저장 등 전통 발효 도구의 계절적 활용을 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"seasonal_ingredient_selection\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 계절별로 달라지는 재료(예: 가을 배추, 여름 고춧가루) 선택이 맛에 미치는 영향을 분석하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"temperature_humidity_effects\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 온도/습도 변화가 발효 속도, 산도, 연화 위험에 미치는 영향을 구체적으로 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"taste_texture_outcome\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 계절별로 달라지는 김치의 산미·아삭함, 된장의 구수함·감칠맛을 구체적으로 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_context_integration\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 전통 발효 문화와 계절성의 결합이 한국 음식의 특유 맛에 미치는 역할을 설명하고 있다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
{"prompt_id": "prompt_ad777d7e74b4", "pair_id": "pair_82dbccc41e9a", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:a30814]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:f1444f]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:106ad5]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:3f8cf6]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating responses to the user's request about modernizing traditional Korean cuisine while keeping its essence. The user provided a reference response and several sample responses. Let me start by understanding the key elements in the reference and samples.\n\nThe reference response talks about fusion cuisine, visual design, healthy ingredients, digital tech, modern cooking techniques, trend fusion, and specific examples. The samples also mention maintaining the core elements like the five tastes (salty, sweet, sour, umami, spicy), using traditional techniques with modern twists, and emphasizing seasonality and regional ingredients.\n\nSo, the criteria should focus on aspects that ensure the response adheres to the core elements of traditional Korean cuisine while incorporating modern elements. Let me think of 8 specific, binary criteria. They need to be prompt-specific and not generic.\n\nFirst, does the response maintain the core elements of traditional Korean cuisine? That's essential. Then, does it use modern techniques? Next, does it incorporate fusion or trends? Also, does it emphasize seasonality and regional ingredients? Maybe, does it address health and sustainability? Also, does it maintain the balance of the five tastes? And finally, does it present a clear, structured approach?\n\nWait, the user's prompt is about modernizing while keeping the essence. So the criteria should check if the response preserves the core aspects (like the five tastes, traditional ingredients, etc.) and introduces modern elements. Let me list possible criteria:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response follow the user's request to modernize while keeping the essence?\n2. Core Elements Preservation: Maintains traditional Korean elements like the five tastes, ingredients, and techniques.\n3. Modern Techniques: Uses contemporary methods like sous-vide, fermentation control, etc.\n4. Fusion/Trend Integration: Combines traditional with modern trends or other cuisines.\n5. Seasonality and Regional Focus: Emphasizes seasonal and local ingredients.\n6. Health and Sustainability: Incorporates healthy, sustainable practices.\n7. Balance of Tastes: Maintains the balance of the five tastes (salty, sweet, sour, umami, spicy).\n8. Structured Approach: Presents a clear, organized method with examples and steps.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary (yes/no) and specific to the prompt. Let me check if these are covered in the samples. The reference and samples all mention maintaining the five tastes, using modern techniques, fusion, seasonality, health aspects, and structured approaches. So these criteria should work. Now, translate these into Korean and assign weights and importance. The reference response is the upper bound, so the criteria should align with that. The importance for each should be essential or important, with weights accordingly. The polarity is positive as they are positive aspects to evaluate.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 전통 한국 요리의 본질(장·발효·불맛·계절성)을 유지하면서 현대화 방법을 구체적으로 제시한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"core_elements_preservation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 간장·된장·고추장, 김치·식초·젓갈, 불맛·육수·식감의 전통적 풍미 축을 명확히 유지한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"modern_techniques\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 저온조리·발효 컨트롤·현대 기술(예: sous-vide, AR)을 전통 요리에 적용하는 구체적 사례를 포함한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"fusion_trend_integration\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 전통 요리와 현대 트렌드(예: 캐주얼 레스토랑, 건강식)를 조화롭게 결합하는 아이디어를 제시한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"seasonality_regionality\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 제철 재료·지역성 재료(예: 토종 곡물, 산나물)를 중심으로 한 메뉴 설계를 포함한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"health_sustainability\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 건강한 재료 사용·부산물 재활용·지속가능한 식재료 선택을 구체적으로 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"taste_balance\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 간장·된장·고추장의 감칠맛, 김치의 산미, 참기름의 고소함 등 전통 풍미의 균형을 유지한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"structured_approach\",\n      \"importance\": \"important\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 메뉴 아이디어·기술·플레이팅·R&D 프로세스를 체계적으로 구성하여 실현 가능성을 보여준다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
