(yes/no), specific to the prompt, and not vague. Let me list possible criteria:\n\n1. **Compliance with regulations**: Whether the response mentions that names aren't mandatory per FIFA rules.\n2. **Tradition/precedent**: If the response refers to historical practices in Europe/South America.\n3. **Operational convenience**: Mentioning cost savings from reusing uniforms.\n4. **Broadcasting alternatives**: Whether the response notes that TV graphics identify players.\n5. **National policy differences**: Highlighting that some countries (like South Korea) always include names.\n6. **Cost/efficiency**: Discussing the cost of printing names for frequent matches.\n7. **Player identification**: Clarifying that it's not about hiding identities but practicality.\n8. **Recent trends**: Mentioning the shift towards including names in some matches.\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me check if these are distinct and specific. Also, need to ensure they are binary. Let me adjust:\n\n1. **Regulation compliance**: Does the response mention that names aren't required by FIFA?\n2. **Tradition**: Does it reference historical practices in Europe/South America?\n3. **Operational efficiency**: Does it discuss cost savings from reusing uniforms?\n4. **Broadcasting alternatives**: Does it note that TV graphics identify players?\n5. **National policy differences**: Does it compare practices between countries?\n6. **Cost/efficiency**: Does it mention the cost of printing names for frequent matches?\n7. **Player identification**: Does it clarify that it's not about hiding identities?\n8. **Trend changes**: Does it mention recent trends towards including names?\n\nWait, some of these might overlap. Let me check the reference and samples again. The reference and samples all mention regulations, tradition, operational convenience, broadcasting, national policies, and recent trends. So maybe the 8 criteria can be:\n\n1. Regulation compliance (FIFA rules)\n2. Tradition/precedent\n3. Operational efficiency (cost/reuse)\n4. Broadcasting alternatives\n5. National policy differences\n6. Player identification (not hiding)\n7. Cost/efficiency (printing costs)\n8. Trend changes (recent shift)\n\nBut need to ensure each is distinct. Maybe combine some. Alternatively, check if the samples have 8 distinct points. The reference and samples all cover these points. So the 8 criteria would be:\n\n1. Regulation compliance (names not mandatory)\n2. Tradition/precedent (historical practices)\n3. Operational efficiency (cost/reuse)\n4. Broadcasting alternatives (TV graphics)\n5. National policy differences (Korea vs others)\n6. Player identification (not hiding)\n7. Cost/efficiency (printing costs)\n8. Trend changes (recent shift)\n\nBut need to make sure each is a separate criterion. Also, the user wants the criteria to be binary. So each should be a yes/no question. Let me structure them as per the example given.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 FIFA 규정에 따라 이름 표기의 의무가 아님을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 유럽/남미의 전통적 관행(이름 없이 번호만 쓰는 전통)을 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 친선전에서 유니폼 재사용 및 비용 절감을 위한 실무적 이유를 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 방송 자막/그래픽을 통해 선수 식별이 가능하다는 점을 명확히 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 한국과 유럽/남미의 정책 차이(이름 표기 유무)를 비교 분석합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '누가 누군지 숨기려는 의도'가 아니라 실무적 이유를 명확히 분별합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 최근 유럽/남미 대표팀의 이름 표기 확대 추세를 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 규정상 의무가 아닌 경기에서 협회 재량을 기반으로 한 관행을 설명합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
