ses, they all have a poetic structure, use natural imagery, and delve into the interaction between humans and nature. So, the rubric should check for elements like adherence to the prompt, use of poetic devices, thematic focus, and coherence.\n\nCriteria could include:\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response address the prompt about the relationship between nature and humans using the two poems?\n2. Thematic Focus: Does it clearly explore the relationship as instructed?\n3. Poetic Devices: Use of metaphors, imagery, etc.\n4. Coherence and Flow: Logical progression of ideas.\n5. Originality: Unique perspective or approach.\n6. Emotional Depth: Conveys emotion or reflection.\n7. Language Quality: Use of vivid, precise language.\n8. Structural Integrity: Proper organization and flow of the prose.\n\nEach criterion needs to be binary. For example, \"Instruction Following\" is essential. Then, \"Thematic Focus\" ensures the topic is addressed. \"Poetic Devices\" checks for literary elements. \"Coherence\" ensures the response is well-structured. \"Originality\" checks for unique ideas. \"Emotional Depth\" assesses the emotional impact. \"Language Quality\" evaluates the use of words. \"Structural Integrity\" ensures the prose is organized.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and not generic. Avoid advice like \"use more vivid language\" but instead check if the response uses such elements. Also, ensure that the rubric is based on the reference response and sample responses, but not copied directly.\n\nNow, translating these into Korean and ensuring they are binary. The reference response seems to be a non-sequitur, so maybe the instruction following is a problem, but the samples are good. So, the rubric should check if the response follows the instruction, uses the right themes, etc.\n\nFinal check: 8 criteria, each with a clear YES/NO, specific to the prompt, not generic.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '꽃'과 '서시'를 모티프로 자연과 인간의 관계를 탐구하는 시적인 산문으로 작성되었는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"thematic_focus\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 자연과 인간의 상호작용, 서시의 시간성, 꽃의 순간성 등을 중심으로 풀어내었는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"poetic_devices\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답에 시적 비유, 은유, 자연 이미지 등이 효과적으로 활용되었는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"coherence\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답의 논리적 흐름과 주제 간 연결성이 명확했는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"originality\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답이 독창적인 시각이나 해석을 제시했는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"emotional_depth\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답이 자연과 인간의 관계를 통해 감정적 통찰을 전달했는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"language_quality\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답의 언어가 시적이고 정교하게 구성되었는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"structural_integrity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답의 구조가 주제에 맞게 조직화되었는지\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
