 checking for issues after cleaning.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all agree that using both is possible but mention specific points like placement, settings, checking for leaks, and sensor positions. The key points from the reference and samples are: instruction following (whether the response addresses the user's question), placement of the dehumidifier, temperature and humidity settings, checking for leaks, sensor positions, and other technical aspects like filter status, drain issues, and cooling performance.\n\nNow, I need to create 8 criteria. Let's start with instruction following. The response must answer whether it's safe to use both devices together and if they can be placed in the same room. That's the first criterion.\n\nNext, placement of the dehumidifier. The reference and samples mention placing it away from the AC's intake. So a criterion about whether the dehumidifier is placed 1.5-2m away from the AC's intake.\n\nThird, temperature settings. The user set the AC to 22°C, but the samples suggest 24-26°C. So a criterion about whether the AC is set to 24-26°C.\n\nFourth, humidity settings. The reference says 50-60% before cleaning, now 80% after. The samples suggest 50-55%. So a criterion about whether the dehumidifier is set to 50-55%.\n\nFifth, checking for leaks. The samples mention checking the drain line for blockages. So a criterion about whether the response mentions checking the drain line for blockages.\n\nSixth, sensor positions. The samples talk about checking the temperature sensor's position. So a criterion about whether the response mentions checking the sensor's position.\n\nSeventh, filter status. The samples mention checking if the filter is dry and properly installed. So a criterion about whether the response mentions checking the filter.\n\nEighth, cooling performance. The samples discuss checking the cooling performance, like the temperature difference between exhaust and intake. So a criterion about whether the response mentions checking the cooling performance.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is binary and specific. Let me check each one again. Instruction following: YES if the response addresses the main question. Placement: YES if the dehumidifier is placed away from AC. Temperature: YES if set to 24-26. Humidity: YES if set to 50-55. Drain check: YES if mentions checking drain. Sensor position: YES if mentions checking sensor. Filter: YES if mentions checking filter. Cooling performance: YES if mentions checking cooling.\n\nThat should cover the main points. Now, structure them into JSON with the required keys.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 에어컨과 제습기 동시 사용의 안전성과 배치 방법을 명확히 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"placement\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"제습기는 에어컨 흡입구로부터 1.5~2m 이상 떨어진 위치에 배치해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"temperature_setting\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"에어컨은 24~26°C로 설정해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"humidity_setting\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"제습기는 목표 습도 50~55%로 설정해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"drain_check\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"실내기 배수 호스가 막히지 않도록 점검해야 합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n  