es are: \n1. Whether the response acknowledges that standard arithmetic doesn't support 1+1=3.\n2. If the response provides a non-standard mathematical structure where 1+1=3 is true.\n3. If the response explains the redefinition of operations or symbols.\n4. If the response uses a specific example (like a ring, modular arithmetic, etc.).\n5. If the response addresses the contradiction or non-standardity of the approach.\n6. If the response clearly distinguishes between standard and non-standard contexts.\n7. If the response provides a logical derivation within a non-standard framework.\n8. If the response avoids fallacies or incorrect proofs.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 binary criteria. Each criterion must be specific to the prompt and checkable as YES/NO. They should be based on the reference and samples, not vague advice.\n\nLooking at the samples, the key elements are: \n- Acknowledging the standard arithmetic contradiction.\n- Providing a non-standard structure.\n- Explaining the redefinition of operations/symbols.\n- Using a specific example (like a ring, modular arithmetic, etc.).\n- Avoiding fallacies.\n- Clearly distinguishing between standard and non-standard.\n- Logical derivation within the non-standard framework.\n- Correctly explaining the non-standard context.\n\nSo, the criteria could be:\n\n1. Acknowledges that standard arithmetic doesn't support 1+1=3.\n2. Provides a non-standard mathematical structure where 1+1=3 is true.\n3. Explains the redefinition of operations or symbols.\n4. Uses a specific example (like a ring, modular arithmetic, etc.).\n5. Avoids fallacies or incorrect proofs.\n6. Clearly distinguishes between standard and non-standard contexts.\n7. Provides a logical derivation within the non-standard framework.\n8. Correctly explains the non-standard context.\n\nEach of these can be checked as YES or NO. For example, if a response doesn't mention standard arithmetic, it's a NO for criterion 1. If it doesn't provide a specific example, it's a NO for criterion 4.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is prompt-specific and binary. Also, avoid generic advice. The reference response and samples all focus on these aspects, so the criteria should align with that.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 표준 산술에서 1+1=3이 거짓임을 인정하고, 비표준 맥락에서 참이 되는 조건을 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"mathematical_structure\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 자명환, 모듈라 산술, 또는 연산 재정의 등 구체적인 수학적 구조를 제시합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"symbol_redefinition\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 기호(숫자, 연산)의 의미를 재정의하여 1+1=3이 참이 되는 방식을 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"logical_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 비표준 맥락에서의 논리적 타당성을 설명하고, 모순이나 오류를 피합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"context_distinction\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 표준 산술과 비표준 맥락을 구분하여 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"example_provision\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 구체적인 예(예: 반올림 규칙, 동형 구조)를 제시합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"non_fallacy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 오류가 있는 증명(예: 0으로 나눔)을 피하고 논리적 타당성을 유지합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"definition_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 비표준 맥락의 정의를 명확히 설명하고, 기호의 재해석을 구체적으로 설명합니다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
