s like \"improve my English\" instead of \"raise my English composition.\"\n\nLooking at the sample responses, common corrections include: using \"looked through\" instead of \"look through,\" \"handouts\" instead of \"printed divide,\" \"rainy season\" instead of \"rains,\" and correct capitalization. Also, the reference response points out that \"for tunately\" should be \"fortunately,\" and \"bexauwe\" is \"because.\"\n\nNow, I need to derive 8 criteria. Let's start with instruction following. The user's response should follow the structure of a diary, including the date, topic, and personal reflections. The reference response includes the date and topic, so that's a criterion.\n\nNext, correct tense. The user used \"look through printed divide teacher tomorro\" which is incorrect. The reference corrects it to \"looked through the handouts my teacher gave us yesterday.\" So, correct past tense for yesterday's actions is important.\n\nThen, proper use of articles. The reference uses \"an English diary\" and \"the rainy season,\" so checking if articles are used correctly is a criterion.\n\nCorrect prepositions. The user wrote \"printed divide teacher tomorro\" which should be \"handouts my teacher gave us yesterday.\" So, correct prepositions like \"handouts\" instead of \"printed divide\" is a criterion.\n\nNatural expressions. The reference uses \"improve my English\" instead of \"raise my English composition,\" so checking for natural expressions is another criterion.\n\nCapitalization. The reference corrects \"I'm\" to \"I’m\" and proper capitalization at the start of sentences. So, correct capitalization is a criterion.\n\nGrammar and spelling. The user has several spelling errors like \"bexauwe\" and \"for tunately,\" which the reference corrects. So, correct grammar and spelling is a criterion.\n\nClarity and coherence. The reference response is clear and coherent, so checking if the response is clear and flows well is another criterion.\n\nWait, that's 7. Let me check again. Maybe I missed one. Let's see:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Includes date, topic, personal reflections.\n2. Correct Tense: Past tense for yesterday's actions.\n3. Proper Articles: Use of \"an\" and \"the.\"\n4. Correct Prepositions: \"handouts\" instead of \"printed divide.\"\n5. Natural Expressions: \"improve my English\" instead of \"raise my composition.\"\n6. Capitalization: Correct capitalization at the start of sentences and proper use of \"I’m.\"\n7. Grammar and Spelling: Correct spelling and grammar.\n8. Clarity and Coherence: The response is clear and flows well.\n\nYes, that's 8. Each is binary, specific, and based on the reference and samples. Now, I need to translate these into Korean with the correct structure.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일기의 구조(날짜, 주제, 개인적 반성)를 포함하고 있어야 합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"tense_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"어제의 행동(예: 유인물 보다)은 과거형으로 표현되어야 합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"article_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"관사(a/an/the) 사용이 적절해야 합니다(예: an English diary, the rainy season).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"preposition_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"적절한 전치사 사용(예: handouts, during the rainy season).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"expression_naturalness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"자연스러운 표현 사용(예: improve my English, make the most of).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"capitalization\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"문장 시작과 I의 대문자 사용이 정확해야 합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"grammar_spelling\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"문법 및 맞춤법 오류가 없어야 합니다(예: fortunately, because).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"coherence_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"문장이 명확하고 논리적으로 연결되어야 합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
