(self-reflection vs. community), and the impact of the colonial period on their works.\n\nSo, the key points from the reference and samples are: instruction following, use of language (standard vs. dialect), themes (self-reflection vs. community), imagery (symbolic vs. concrete), structure (free verse vs. narrative), historical context integration, emotional tone (melancholic vs. hopeful), and the balance between personal and collective identity.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 specific criteria. Each should be a binary yes/no question. Let me list them out:\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response address the comparison of the two poets and the impact of the colonial period on their works?\n2. **Language Use**: Does the response mention the use of standard Korean vs. dialects or local language?\n3. **Themes**: Does the response highlight the contrast between self-reflection and community focus?\n4. **Imagery**: Does the response use symbolic imagery (like stars, night sky) vs. concrete, everyday imagery?\n5. **Structure**: Does the response discuss the structure of their poetry (free verse vs. narrative style)?\n6. **Historical Context**: Does the response integrate the historical context of the colonial period into the analysis?\n7. **Emotional Tone**: Does the response reflect a melancholic or hopeful tone in their works?\n8. **Balance of Identity**: Does the response balance personal identity with collective identity in their works?\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and not generic. Also, the criteria should be in Korean as per the user's request. Let me check if these are binary and if they are specific enough. Yes, each can be answered with a yes or no. Now, I'll structure them into the JSON format as specified.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 윤동주와 백석의 시를 비교하며, 일제강점기의 영향을 분석하는 주제를 명확히 다룬다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"language_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 시인의 언어 전략(표준어 vs. 방언, 토착어)을 구체적으로 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"theme_comparison\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 시인의 주제 차이(자기 성찰 vs. 공동체 보존)를 명확히 구분한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"imagery_type\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 상징적 이미지(별, 하늘)와 구체적 이미지(방언, 음식)의 차이를 분석한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"structure_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 시인의 형식(자유시 vs. 서사적 구술)을 비교적으로 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 일제강점기의 역사적 압력(검열, 언어 정책)을 작품 세계에 미친 영향을 다룬다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"emotional_tone\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 시인의 감정적 정조(우울 vs. 희망)를 구체적으로 분석한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"identity_balance\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 개인적 정체성과 공동체 정체성의 균형을 작품 세계에서 확인한다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
