ual variation, logical consistency, and clarity.\n\nLet me list possible criteria:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response address the question and explain the reasoning steps?\n2. Assumption Validity: Are the assumptions (like blink rate, awake hours, lifespan) reasonable and consistent?\n3. Step-by-Step Explanation: Does the response break down the calculation into clear steps?\n4. Numerical Accuracy: Are the numbers calculated correctly based on the assumptions?\n5. Unit Consistency: Are all units (hours, days, years) used correctly and consistently?\n6. Acknowledgment of Variation: Does the response mention that individual differences can affect the estimate?\n7. Logical Consistency: Are the calculations logically sound and free from errors?\n8. Clarity and Conciseness: Is the explanation clear and not overly complicated?\n\nNow, I need to make sure each criterion is binary (YES/NO) and specific to the prompt. Also, avoid vague advice. Let me check if these are all prompt-specific and binary. For example, \"acknowledgment of variation\" is a yes/no check. Each of these can be evaluated as a simple yes or no. The reference response includes all these elements, so the criteria should align with that.\n\nI need to assign importance and weight. The reference response emphasizes step-by-step reasoning and correct calculations, so those might have higher weights. But the user said to use the reference as a guide, so the criteria should reflect what's in the reference. Also, the sample responses vary in how they present the steps and assumptions, so the criteria should capture that.\n\nLet me structure each criterion with the correct text in Korean, ensuring they are specific and binary. For example, \"Step-by-Step Explanation\" would check if the response breaks down the calculation into clear steps. \"Numerical Accuracy\" would check if the math is correct based on the assumptions.\n\nI think that's all. Now, format them into JSON as specified.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 질문에 대한 단계별 추론을 포함하고 있으며, 계산 과정을 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"assumption_validity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 합리적인 가정(예: 분당 깜빡임 빈도, 수명)을 명시하고 이를 기반으로 계산합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"step_by_step_explanation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 계산 과정을 명확한 단계로 나누어 설명합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"numerical_accuracy\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 수치 계산이 정확하게 이루어졌는지 확인합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"unit_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시간 단위(분, 시간, 년)가 일관되게 사용되었는지 확인합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"variation_acknowledgment\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 개인차(예: 환경, 건강)가 결과에 영향을 미칠 수 있음을 언급합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"logical_consistency\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 계산 논리가 타당하고 오류가 없는지 확인합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"clarity_and_conciseness\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 설명이 명확하고 과도한 복잡성 없이 전달되었는지 확인합니다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
