tructured approach, breaking down the comparison into sections like historical context, spatial organization, materials, decoration, etc. Each sample response has a clear, organized structure with specific points.\n\nNow, I need to identify the key aspects that are essential for a good response. The reference response and samples emphasize several elements: historical context, architectural layout (axis and symmetry), materials and construction techniques, decorative elements and symbolism, spatial organization (public vs. private areas), cultural and political symbolism, and the expression of power through design.\n\nLet me list possible criteria:\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response directly address the comparison of design, decoration, and power/culture expression?\n2. **Historical Context**: Does it provide accurate historical background for both palaces?\n3. **Architectural Layout**: Does it discuss the spatial organization and symmetry?\n4. **Materials and Construction**: Does it mention the materials used and their significance?\n5. **Decorative Elements**: Does it cover the decorative features and their symbolism?\n6. **Cultural and Political Symbolism**: Does it link the design to the cultural and political aspects of each country?\n7. **Spatial Organization**: Does it differentiate between public and private spaces?\n8. **Expression of Power**: Does it explain how the design reflects the power and culture of each country?\n\nNow, I need to ensure these criteria are binary (YES/NO) and specific. Let me check each against the reference and samples.\n\nFor example, \"Instruction Following\" is essential because the response must directly address the user's request. The reference and samples all do that, so a YES would be appropriate.\n\n\"Historical Context\" is covered in the reference, so a YES if the response includes that.\n\n\"Architectural Layout\" is addressed in the samples, so YES.\n\n\"Materials and Construction\" is part of the analysis in the samples, so YES.\n\n\"Decorative Elements\" is covered in the samples, so YES.\n\n\"Cultural and Political Symbolism\" is a key part of the reference and samples, so YES.\n\n\"Spatial Organization\" is discussed in the samples, so YES.\n\n\"Expression of Power\" is a central theme in the samples, so YES.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific and not generic. For example, \"Cultural and Political Symbolism\" is specific to the prompt's request. Each criterion should be a binary check.\n\nNow, I'll structure the JSON with these criteria, ensuring they are in the correct format and that each has an ID, axis, importance, weight, polarity, and text in Korean.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 경복궁과 베르사유의 디자인, 장식, 권력·문화 표현을 비교 분석하는 데 집중하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"historical_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 궁전의 창건 시기와 역사적 배경을 명확히 설명하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"spatial_organization\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 건축물의 배치 구조(외전/내전, 축선, 정원 등)를 구체적으로 분석하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"materials_and_construction\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 목조·석조, 기와지붕, 재료의 상징성 등을 구체적으로 설명하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"decorative_elements\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 단청, 금박, 신화적 장식 요소(용·봉황, 태양왕 등)를 문화적 상징으로 분석하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"cultural_political_symbolism\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 궁전이 나타내는 국가의 권력 구조(유교적 질서 vs. 절대왕정)를 건축 언어로 구체적으로 드러내고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"power_expression\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 건축물이 권력의 시각적 표현(조화 vs. 스펙터클)을 공간적으로 구현하는 방식을 비교하고 있다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"comparative_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 궁전의 디자인·장식·문화적 의미를 통합적으로 비교하며, 공통점과 차이점을 명확히 제시하고 있다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
