working towards a more just society.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all address the user's feelings of unfairness and the concept of fate. They offer advice on coping mechanisms, like focusing on small actions, reducing comparisons, and seeking support. Each response acknowledges the pain of unfairness but suggests ways to move forward.\n\nNow, I need to identify the key aspects that the reference response emphasizes. The reference response talks about understanding fate, the inherent unfairness of the world, the importance of personal and collective action towards fairness, and the value of empathy and connection.\n\nSo, possible criteria could be:\n\n1. Acknowledgment of the concept of fate and its inevitability.\n2. Recognition of the inherent unfairness in the world.\n3. Suggestion of personal actions to combat unfairness.\n4. Emphasis on empathy and understanding towards others.\n5. Encouragement of collective efforts towards fairness.\n6. Addressing the emotional impact of unfairness.\n7. Providing practical steps for coping with the situation.\n8. Balancing acceptance of fate with proactive steps.\n\nWait, but the criteria need to be binary and specific. Let me refine these. For example:\n\n- Does the response acknowledge the concept of fate as an unchangeable force?\n- Does it recognize the inherent unfairness in the world?\n- Does it suggest personal actions to address the unfairness?\n- Does it emphasize empathy and understanding towards others?\n- Does it encourage collective efforts towards fairness?\n- Does it address the emotional impact of the situation?\n- Does it provide practical steps for coping?\n- Does it balance acceptance of fate with proactive steps?\n\nBut I need to make sure each criterion is specific to the prompt and can be evaluated as YES/NO. Let me check each sample response to see what they include.\n\nLooking at the sample responses, they all mention the concept of fate, the unfairness, and suggest actions like reducing comparisons, seeking support, and small acts of kindness. They also address the emotional aspect and balance acceptance with proactive steps.\n\nSo, the criteria should be:\n\n1. Acknowledgment of fate as an unchangeable force.\n2. Recognition of inherent unfairness in the world.\n3. Suggestion of personal actions to combat unfairness.\n4. Emphasis on empathy and understanding towards others.\n5. Encouragement of collective efforts towards fairness.\n6. Addressing the emotional impact of unfairness.\n7. Providing practical steps for coping with the situation.\n8. Balancing acceptance of fate with proactive steps.\n\nEach of these can be evaluated as YES or NO. Now, I need to translate these into Korean and ensure they are specific to the prompt. Also, check that they are not generic. For example, \"emphasizing empathy\" is specific to the prompt's context of dealing with unfairness and fate.\n\nI think these eight criteria cover the key aspects of the reference response and the sample responses. Each is binary and specific. Now, I'll structure them into the JSON format as specified.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '운명'이라는 개념을 인식하고, 그에 대한 인식을 인정하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 세상의 불공정함을 인식하고, 그에 대한 감정적 반응을 인정하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 개인적 행동을 제안하며, 불공정함을 극복하는 실천적 방안을 제시하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 타인의 감정을 공감하고, 상대의 입장을 존중하는 태도를 강조하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 집단적 노력이나 사회적 변화를 위한 제안을 포함하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 감정적 슬픔이나 억울함을 인정하고, 그에 대한 정서적 지지를 제안하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 구체적인 실천적 조언(예: 비교 줄이기, 감사 기록 등)을 제공하는지\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 운명에 굴복하지만, 동시에 개인의 주도적 선택을 강조하는 균형을 유지하는지\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
