 stocks and bonds.\n\nNow, looking at the sample responses, they all provide detailed explanations, including the yield curve, how different types of bonds react to rate changes, and how stocks are affected. They also mention specific scenarios like steepening, flattening, and inversion of the yield curve, and how these affect different sectors.\n\nThe main criteria should focus on whether the response addresses each of these aspects. Let me think of 8 specific points:\n\n1. **Instruction Following**: Does the response directly address the user's request about interest rates and their impact on stocks and bonds?\n2. **Definition of Interest Rates**: Does it clearly define what interest rates are?\n3. **Factors Influencing Interest Rates**: Does it mention factors like economic health and inflation?\n4. **Short-Term vs. Long-Term Rates**: Does it explain the difference between short and long-term rates?\n5. **Yield Curve Explanation**: Does it discuss the yield curve and its implications?\n6. **Impact on Bonds**: Does it explain how bond prices react to interest rate changes?\n7. **Impact on Stocks**: Does it cover how stocks are affected by interest rate changes?\n8. **Yield Curve Interpretation**: Does it interpret the yield curve's changes (steepening, flattening, inversion) and their economic signals?\n\nEach of these should be a binary check. Let me make sure they are specific and not generic. For example, \"explains the yield curve\" is specific, as is \"mentions factors like economic health and inflation.\"\n\nI need to ensure that each criterion is tied directly to the user's query and that the response must meet all these points to be considered high quality. The reference response covers all these, so the criteria should reflect that.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 금리의 의미와 장단기 금리차가 주식·채권에 미치는 영향을 완전히 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"definition_clarity\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 금리의 정의(돈의 시간가치, 이자 비율)를 명확히 제시한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"factor_influence\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 금리가 경기·물가·정책 기대에 영향을 받는다는 점을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"term_diff_explained\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 장기 금리(10년 이상)와 단기 금리(1년 이하)의 구분을 명확히 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"yield_curve_analysis\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 수익률 곡선(정상, 평탄, 역전)의 의미와 경기 예측 신호를 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"bond_impact\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 금리 상승 시 채권가격 하락, 장기채의 민감도를 명확히 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"stock_impact\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 금리 상승 시 주식 시장의 변동성과 섹터별 반응(금융·방어주)을 설명한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"signal_interpretation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 수익률 곡선의 변화(스티프닝·플래트닝·역전)를 경기 신호로 해석한다.\",\n      \"self_contained\": true\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
