 all recommend checking official sources. So, \"Does the response suggest further steps to obtain the most accurate data (e.g., contacting official sources)?\" Yes or no.\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me check if these are all distinct and specific. Maybe some overlap. Let me rephrase to ensure they are unique. For example, the first is instruction following, the second is acknowledging difficulty, third is providing ranges, fourth is official sources, fifth is seasonal variation, sixth is factors affecting numbers, seventh is historical context, eighth is suggesting further steps. That's eight. Each is binary and specific. I think that works. Now, I need to make sure each is in Korean, and the JSON structure is correct. Also, the importance and weight are set, but the user didn't specify, so maybe just set them as essential with weights. The polarity is positive. Self-contained is true. Alright, that should cover it.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 '성수기 여름 기간 동안 해운대 해수욕장 방문객 수'에 직접적으로 답변합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"acknowledgment_of_limitations\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.25,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 정확한 수치 제공의 어려움을 인정하고 대체적 출처를 제시합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"approximate_range_provision\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.15,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 성수기 방문객 수에 대한 대략적인 범위를 제공합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"official_source_recommendation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.1,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 부산관광공사나 해운대구청 등 공식 출처를 추천합니다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\