the response address both form and aesthetic transformation?\n2. Structural Comparison: Does it compare the structure of sijo and modern free verse?\n3. Rhythm and Meter: Does it discuss rhythm differences?\n4. Imagery and Symbolism: Does it compare imagery used in both forms?\n5. Language and Diction: Does it mention language differences?\n6. Aesthetic Transformation: Does it explain how traditional aesthetics are transformed?\n7. Use of Form: Does it discuss the use of form in both?\n8. Conclusion on Continuity: Does it conclude on the continuity of traditional aesthetics?\n\nWait, but the user wants 8 criteria. Let me check again. The reference response mentions structure, visual imagery, and word choice. The samples talk about form, rhythm, imagery, language, and transformation. So maybe:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Correctly addresses both form and transformation.\n2. Structural Comparison: Compares structure of sijo and modern free verse.\n3. Rhythm and Meter: Discusses rhythm differences.\n4. Imagery and Symbolism: Compares imagery used.\n5. Language and Diction: Mentions language differences.\n6. Aesthetic Transformation: Explains transformation of traditional aesthetics.\n7. Use of Form: Discusses form in both.\n8. Conclusion on Continuity: Concludes on continuity of traditional aesthetics.\n\nBut need to make sure each is binary and specific. Also, avoid generic advice. Let me adjust:\n\n1. Instruction Following: Does the response address both form and aesthetic transformation?\n2. Structural Comparison: Does it compare the structure of sijo and modern free verse?\n3. Rhythm and Meter: Does it discuss rhythm differences?\n4. Imagery and Symbolism: Does it compare imagery used in both forms?\n5. Language and Diction: Does it mention language differences?\n6. Aesthetic Transformation: Does it explain how traditional aesthetics are transformed?\n7. Use of Form: Does it discuss the use of form in both?\n8. Conclusion on Continuity: Does it conclude on the continuity of traditional aesthetics?\n\nYes, these seem specific and binary. Now, translate these into Korean with the required JSON structure.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조와 현대 단시의 형식적 특징을 비교하고, 전통 시가의 미학이 현대 시에 어떻게 계승되고 변주되는지를 모두 다룬다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"structural_comparison\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조의 3장 구조와 현대 단시의 자유 구조를 구체적으로 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"rhythm_meter\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조의 규칙적 음보율과 현대 단시의 자유 리듬을 구체적으로 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"imagery_symbolism\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조의 자연 상징과 현대 단시의 도시 이미지 사용을 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"language_diction\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조의 절제된 어조와 현대 단시의 구어·전문어 혼용을 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"aesthetic_transformation\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 전통 시가의 미학이 현대 시에 어떻게 변주되는지를 구체적으로 설명한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"form_usage\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 시조의 정형식과 현대 단시의 자유 형식 사용을 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"continuity_conclusion\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n   