{"prompt_id": "prompt_c03bcda3cbb1", "pair_id": "pair_fd1a19cd4bca", "method": "rrd_pairwise_reference", "generator_family": "qwen_small", "generator_model": "Qwen/Qwen3-4B-FP8", "criteria": [{"id": "F1", "axis": "instruction_following", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사용자 요청을 직접적이고 빠짐없이 수행한다. [smoke:f6a93d]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F2", "axis": "correctness", "importance": "essential", "weight": 0.2941176470588235, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 사실 오류와 근거 없는 단정을 피하고 정확한 내용을 제공한다. [smoke:b079f9]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F3", "axis": "completeness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 핵심 요소를 누락하지 않고 필요한 설명을 포함한다. [smoke:3d16aa]", "self_contained": true}, {"id": "F4", "axis": "korean_naturalness", "importance": "important", "weight": 0.20588235294117643, "polarity": "positive", "text_ko": "응답은 자연스럽고 읽기 쉬운 한국어 문장을 사용한다. [smoke:edc82d]", "self_contained": true}], "rar_items": [], "generation_metadata": {"fallback_used": "rrd_static_fallback", "errors": ["'\"satisfied\"'"], "auxiliary_sample_ids": ["sample_01", "sample_02", "sample_03", "sample_04", "sample_05", "sample_06", "sample_07", "sample_08"], "reference_guidance_used": true, "raw_output": "<think>\nOkay, I need to create a JSON with 8 criteria for evaluating the responses to the user's query about comparing the love themes in \"So Nakgi\" and \"Dongbaekkot\" by Hwang Sun-won and Kim Yu-jeong, focusing on how they portray love in rural settings. The criteria must be specific to the prompt, binary (YES/NO), and not vague or generic.\n\nFirst, I'll look at the reference response and sample responses to understand what's important. The reference response talks about the nature of love, the use of imagery, the role of rural settings, and the contrast between the two authors' approaches. The sample responses also mention elements like the tone, narrative perspective, use of symbolism, and the social context.\n\nSo, the key points from the reference and samples are: instruction following, use of imagery, narrative perspective, social context, symbolism, emotional tone, contrast between the two authors, and the role of rural setting in shaping love.\n\nNow, I need to translate these into 8 specific, binary criteria. Let's start with instruction following. The response must directly address comparing the love themes and analyzing the rural setting differences. So, \"instruction_following\" is essential.\n\nNext, \"use_of_imagery\" – does the response use vivid imagery to represent love and rural settings? The reference and samples use a lot of imagery, so this is important.\n\nThen, \"narrative_perspective\" – does the response correctly use 3rd person for Hwang and 1st person for Kim? The samples mention different perspectives, so this is a key point.\n\n\"social_context\" – does the response analyze how social factors like class or community influence love? The samples discuss social aspects, so this is a criterion.\n\n\"symbolism\" – does the response use symbols like the rain in \"So Nakgi\" and the plum blossom in \"Dongbaekkot\"? The reference and samples use symbols, so this is important.\n\n\"emotional_tone\" – does the response contrast the tragic tone of Hwang with the humorous tone of Kim? The samples mention different tones, so this is a criterion.\n\n\"contrast_between_authors\" – does the response clearly contrast the two authors' approaches? The samples do this, so this is essential.\n\nLastly, \"rural_setting_role\" – does the response explain how the rural setting shapes love in each work? The samples discuss the role of rural settings, so this is a key criterion.\n\nI need to make sure each criterion is specific, binary, and not generic. Let me check each one again to ensure they fit the requirements.\n</think>\n\n{\n  \"criteria\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R1\",\n      \"axis\": \"instruction_following\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.5,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 황순원과 김유정의 소나기 및 동백꽃에서 드러난 사랑의 양상을 비교하고, 두 작가가 농촌 배경을 통해 사랑을 그려낸 방식의 차이를 분석하는 데 집중한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R2\",\n      \"axis\": \"use_of_imagery\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.3,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 자연 요소(소나기, 개울, 동백꽃)를 상징적 이미지로 활용하여 사랑의 정서와 농촌 배경을 시각화한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R3\",\n      \"axis\": \"narrative_perspective\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 황순원의 3인칭 제한 시점과 김유정의 1인칭 사내아이 화자 시점의 차이를 명확히 구분한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R4\",\n      \"axis\": \"social_context\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 농촌의 계층 차이(도회-농촌), 공동체 관습, 가난 등 사회적 맥락이 사랑의 형성에 미친 영향을 분석한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R5\",\n      \"axis\": \"symbolism\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 소나기(첫사랑의 비극성), 동백꽃(생동감의 희극성)을 상징적 구조로 해석하여 사랑의 본질을 드러낸다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R6\",\n      \"axis\": \"emotional_tone\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 황순원의 서정적 비극성과 김유정의 해학적 생동감을 명확히 구분하여 감정의 정조를 비교한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R7\",\n      \"axis\": \"contrast_between_authors\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 두 작가의 사랑 표현 방식(서정적 상징 vs 생활적 해학)과 농촌 배경 활용 방식(정화된 자연 vs 현실적 생활)의 차이를 명확히 분석한다.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"R8\",\n      \"axis\": \"rural_setting_role\",\n      \"importance\": \"essential\",\n      \"weight\": 0.2,\n      \"polarity\": \"positive\",\n      \"text_ko\": \"응답은 농촌이 사랑의 서정적 공명판(황순원)과 생활적 무대(김유정)로 기능하는 방식을 구체적으로 설명한다.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"}}
